5024 "invalid operands of types %qT and %qT to binary %qO",
5025 TREE_TYPE (orig_op0), TREE_TYPE (orig_op1), code);
5026 return error_mark_node;
5027 }
5028
5029 /* If we're in a template, the only thing we need to know is the
5030 RESULT_TYPE. */
5031 if (processing_template_decl)
5032 {
5033 /* Since the middle-end checks the type when doing a build2, we
5034 need to build the tree in pieces. This built tree will never
5035 get out of the front-end as we replace it when instantiating
5036 the template. */
5037 tree tmp = build2 (resultcode,
5038 build_type ? build_type : result_type,
5039 NULL_TREE, op1);
5040 TREE_OPERAND (tmp, 0) = op0;
5041 return tmp;
5042 }
5043
5044 /* Remember the original type; RESULT_TYPE might be changed later on
5045 by shorten_binary_op. */
5046 tree orig_type = result_type;
5047
5048 if (arithmetic_types_p)
5049 {
5050 bool first_complex = (code0 == COMPLEX_TYPE);
5051 bool second_complex = (code1 == COMPLEX_TYPE);
5052 int none_complex = (!first_complex && !second_complex);
5053
5054 /* Adapted from patch for c/24581. */
5055 if (first_complex != second_complex
5056 && (code == PLUS_EXPR
5057 || code == MINUS_EXPR
5058 || code == MULT_EXPR
5059 || (code == TRUNC_DIV_EXPR && first_complex))
5060 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (result_type)) == REAL_TYPE
5061 && flag_signed_zeros)
5062 {
5063 /* An operation on mixed real/complex operands must be
5064 handled specially, but the language-independent code can
5065 more easily optimize the plain complex arithmetic if
5066 -fno-signed-zeros. */
5067 tree real_type = TREE_TYPE (result_type);
5068 tree real, imag;
5069 if (first_complex)
5070 {
5071 if (TREE_TYPE (op0) != result_type)
5072 op0 = cp_convert_and_check (result_type, op0, complain);
5073 if (TREE_TYPE (op1) != real_type)
5074 op1 = cp_convert_and_check (real_type, op1, complain);
5075 }
5076 else
5077 {
5078 if (TREE_TYPE (op0) != real_type)
5079 op0 = cp_convert_and_check (real_type, op0, complain);
5080 if (TREE_TYPE (op1) != result_type)
5081 op1 = cp_convert_and_check (result_type, op1, complain);
5082 }
5083 if (TREE_CODE (op0) == ERROR_MARK || TREE_CODE (op1) == ERROR_MARK)
5084 return error_mark_node;
5085 if (first_complex)
5086 {
5087 op0 = save_expr (op0);
5088 real = cp_build_unary_op (REALPART_EXPR, op0, true, complain);
5089 imag = cp_build_unary_op (IMAGPART_EXPR, op0, true, complain);
5090 switch (code)
5091 {
5092 case MULT_EXPR:
5093 case TRUNC_DIV_EXPR:
5094 op1 = save_expr (op1);
5095 imag = build2 (resultcode, real_type, imag, op1);
5096 /* Fall through. */
5097 case PLUS_EXPR:
5098 case MINUS_EXPR:
5099 real = build2 (resultcode, real_type, real, op1);
5100 break;
5101 default:
5102 gcc_unreachable();
5103 }
5104 }
5105 else
5106 {
5107 op1 = save_expr (op1);
5108 real = cp_build_unary_op (REALPART_EXPR, op1, true, complain);
5109 imag = cp_build_unary_op (IMAGPART_EXPR, op1, true, complain);
5110 switch (code)
5111 {
5112 case MULT_EXPR:
5113 op0 = save_expr (op0);
5114 imag = build2 (resultcode, real_type, op0, imag);
5115 /* Fall through. */
5116 case PLUS_EXPR:
5117 real = build2 (resultcode, real_type, op0, real);
5118 break;
5119 case MINUS_EXPR:
5120 real = build2 (resultcode, real_type, op0, real);
5121 imag = build1 (NEGATE_EXPR, real_type, imag);
5122 break;
5123 default:
5124 gcc_unreachable();
5125 }
5126 }
5127 result = build2 (COMPLEX_EXPR, result_type, real, imag);
5128 return result;
5129 }
5130
5131 /* For certain operations (which identify themselves by shorten != 0)
5132 if both args were extended from the same smaller type,
5133 do the arithmetic in that type and then extend.
5134
5135 shorten !=0 and !=1 indicates a bitwise operation.
5136 For them, this optimization is safe only if
5137 both args are zero-extended or both are sign-extended.
5138 Otherwise, we might change the result.
5139 E.g., (short)-1 | (unsigned short)-1 is (int)-1
5140 but calculated in (unsigned short) it would be (unsigned short)-1. */
5141
5142 if (shorten && none_complex)
5143 {
5144 final_type = result_type;
5145 result_type = shorten_binary_op (result_type, op0, op1,
5146 shorten == -1);
5147 }
5148
5149 /* Comparison operations are shortened too but differently.
5150 They identify themselves by setting short_compare = 1. */
5151
5152 if (short_compare)
5153 {
5154 /* We call shorten_compare only for diagnostic-reason. */
5155 tree xop0 = fold_simple (op0), xop1 = fold_simple (op1),
5156 xresult_type = result_type;
5157 enum tree_code xresultcode = resultcode;
5158 shorten_compare (location, &xop0, &xop1, &xresult_type,
5159 &xresultcode);
5160 }
5161
5162 if ((short_compare || code == MIN_EXPR || code == MAX_EXPR)
5163 && warn_sign_compare
5164 /* Do not warn until the template is instantiated; we cannot
5165 bound the ranges of the arguments until that point. */
5166 && !processing_template_decl
5167 && (complain & tf_warning)
5168 && c_inhibit_evaluation_warnings == 0
5169 /* Even unsigned enum types promote to signed int. We don't
5170 want to issue -Wsign-compare warnings for this case. */
5171 && !enum_cast_to_int (orig_op0)
5172 && !enum_cast_to_int (orig_op1))
5173 {
5174 tree oop0 = maybe_constant_value (orig_op0);
5175 tree oop1 = maybe_constant_value (orig_op1);
5176
5177 if (TREE_CODE (oop0) != INTEGER_CST)
5178 oop0 = cp_fully_fold (orig_op0);
5179 if (TREE_CODE (oop1) != INTEGER_CST)
5180 oop1 = cp_fully_fold (orig_op1);
5181 warn_for_sign_compare (location, oop0, oop1, op0, op1,
5182 result_type, resultcode);
5183 }
5184 }
5185
5186 /* If CONVERTED is zero, both args will be converted to type RESULT_TYPE.
5187 Then the expression will be built.
5188 It will be given type FINAL_TYPE if that is nonzero;
5189 otherwise, it will be given type RESULT_TYPE. */
5190 if (! converted)
5191 {
5192 if (TREE_TYPE (op0) != result_type)
5193 op0 = cp_convert_and_check (result_type, op0, complain);
5194 if (TREE_TYPE (op1) != result_type)
5195 op1 = cp_convert_and_check (result_type, op1, complain);
5196
5197 if (op0 == error_mark_node || op1 == error_mark_node)
5198 return error_mark_node;
5199 }
5200
5201 if (build_type == NULL_TREE)
5202 build_type = result_type;
5203
5204 if ((flag_sanitize & (SANITIZE_SHIFT | SANITIZE_DIVIDE
5205 | SANITIZE_FLOAT_DIVIDE))
5206 && !processing_template_decl
5207 && do_ubsan_in_current_function ()
5208 && (doing_div_or_mod || doing_shift))
5209 {
5210 /* OP0 and/or OP1 might have side-effects. */
5211 op0 = cp_save_expr (op0);
5212 op1 = cp_save_expr (op1);
5213 op0 = fold_non_dependent_expr (op0);
5214 op1 = fold_non_dependent_expr (op1);
5215 if (doing_div_or_mod && (flag_sanitize & (SANITIZE_DIVIDE
5216 | SANITIZE_FLOAT_DIVIDE)))
5217 {
5218 /* For diagnostics we want to use the promoted types without
5219 shorten_binary_op. So convert the arguments to the
5220 original result_type. */
5221 tree cop0 = op0;
5222 tree cop1 = op1;
5223 if (TREE_TYPE (cop0) != orig_type)
5224 cop0 = cp_convert (orig_type, op0, complain);
5225 if (TREE_TYPE (cop1) != orig_type)
5226 cop1 = cp_convert (orig_type, op1, complain);
5227 instrument_expr = ubsan_instrument_division (location, cop0, cop1);
5228 }
5229 else if (doing_shift && (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_SHIFT))
5230 instrument_expr = ubsan_instrument_shift (location, code, op0, op1);
5231 }
5232
5233 result = build2_loc (location, resultcode, build_type, op0, op1);
5234 if (final_type != 0)
5235 result = cp_convert (final_type, result, complain);
5236
5237 if (instrument_expr != NULL)
5238 result = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (result),
5239 instrument_expr, result);
5240
5241 if (!processing_template_decl)
5242 {
5243 op0 = cp_fully_fold (op0);
5244 /* Only consider the second argument if the first isn't overflowed. */
5245 if (!CONSTANT_CLASS_P (op0) || TREE_OVERFLOW_P (op0))
5246 return result;
5247 op1 = cp_fully_fold (op1);
5248 if (!CONSTANT_CLASS_P (op1) || TREE_OVERFLOW_P (op1))
5249 return result;
5250 }
5251 else if (!CONSTANT_CLASS_P (op0) || !CONSTANT_CLASS_P (op1)
5252 || TREE_OVERFLOW_P (op0) || TREE_OVERFLOW_P (op1))
5253 return result;
5254
5255 result_ovl = fold_build2 (resultcode, build_type, op0, op1);
5256 if (TREE_OVERFLOW_P (result_ovl))
5257 overflow_warning (location, result_ovl);
5258
5259 return result;
5260}
5261
5262/* Build a VEC_PERM_EXPR.
5263 This is a simple wrapper for c_build_vec_perm_expr. */
5264tree
5265build_x_vec_perm_expr (location_t loc,
5266 tree arg0, tree arg1, tree arg2,
5267 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5268{
5269 tree orig_arg0 = arg0;
5270 tree orig_arg1 = arg1;
5271 tree orig_arg2 = arg2;
5272 if (processing_template_decl)
5273 {
5274 if (type_dependent_expression_p (arg0)
5275 || type_dependent_expression_p (arg1)
5276 || type_dependent_expression_p (arg2))
5277 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, VEC_PERM_EXPR, arg0, arg1, arg2);
5278 arg0 = build_non_dependent_expr (arg0);
5279 if (arg1)
5280 arg1 = build_non_dependent_expr (arg1);
5281 arg2 = build_non_dependent_expr (arg2);
5282 }
5283 tree exp = c_build_vec_perm_expr (loc, arg0, arg1, arg2, complain & tf_error);
5284 if (processing_template_decl && exp != error_mark_node)
5285 return build_min_non_dep (VEC_PERM_EXPR, exp, orig_arg0,
5286 orig_arg1, orig_arg2);
5287 return exp;
5288}
5289
5290/* Return a tree for the sum or difference (RESULTCODE says which)
5291 of pointer PTROP and integer INTOP. */
5292
5293static tree
5294cp_pointer_int_sum (location_t loc, enum tree_code resultcode, tree ptrop,
5295 tree intop, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5296{
5297 tree res_type = TREE_TYPE (ptrop);
5298
5299 /* pointer_int_sum() uses size_in_bytes() on the TREE_TYPE(res_type)
5300 in certain circumstance (when it's valid to do so). So we need
5301 to make sure it's complete. We don't need to check here, if we
5302 can actually complete it at all, as those checks will be done in
5303 pointer_int_sum() anyway. */
5304 complete_type (TREE_TYPE (res_type));
5305
5306 return pointer_int_sum (loc, resultcode, ptrop,
5307 intop, complain & tf_warning_or_error);
5308}
5309
5310/* Return a tree for the difference of pointers OP0 and OP1.
5311 The resulting tree has type int. */
5312
5313static tree
5314pointer_diff (location_t loc, tree op0, tree op1, tree ptrtype,
5315 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5316{
5317 tree result;
5318 tree restype = ptrdiff_type_node;
5319 tree target_type = TREE_TYPE (ptrtype);
5320
5321 if (!complete_type_or_else (target_type, NULL_TREE))
5322 return error_mark_node;
5323
5324 if (VOID_TYPE_P (target_type))
5325 {
5326 if (complain & tf_error)
5327 permerror (loc, "ISO C++ forbids using pointer of "
5328 "type %<void *%> in subtraction");
5329 else
5330 return error_mark_node;
5331 }
5332 if (TREE_CODE (target_type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
5333 {
5334 if (complain & tf_error)
5335 permerror (loc, "ISO C++ forbids using pointer to "
5336 "a function in subtraction");
5337 else
5338 return error_mark_node;
5339 }
5340 if (TREE_CODE (target_type) == METHOD_TYPE)
5341 {
5342 if (complain & tf_error)
5343 permerror (loc, "ISO C++ forbids using pointer to "
5344 "a method in subtraction");
5345 else
5346 return error_mark_node;
5347 }
5348
5349 /* First do the subtraction as integers;
5350 then drop through to build the divide operator. */
5351
5352 op0 = cp_build_binary_op (loc,
5353 MINUS_EXPR,
5354 cp_convert (restype, op0, complain),
5355 cp_convert (restype, op1, complain),
5356 complain);
5357
5358 /* This generates an error if op1 is a pointer to an incomplete type. */
5359 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (op1))))
5360 {
5361 if (complain & tf_error)
5362 error_at (loc, "invalid use of a pointer to an incomplete type in "
5363 "pointer arithmetic");
5364 else
5365 return error_mark_node;
5366 }
5367
5368 if (pointer_to_zero_sized_aggr_p (TREE_TYPE (op1)))
5369 {
5370 if (complain & tf_error)
5371 error_at (loc, "arithmetic on pointer to an empty aggregate");
5372 else
5373 return error_mark_node;
5374 }
5375
5376 op1 = (TYPE_PTROB_P (ptrtype)
5377 ? size_in_bytes_loc (loc, target_type)
5378 : integer_one_node);
5379
5380 /* Do the division. */
5381
5382 result = build2_loc (loc, EXACT_DIV_EXPR, restype, op0,
5383 cp_convert (restype, op1, complain));
5384 return result;
5385}
5386
5387/* Construct and perhaps optimize a tree representation
5388 for a unary operation. CODE, a tree_code, specifies the operation
5389 and XARG is the operand. */
5390
5391tree
5392build_x_unary_op (location_t loc, enum tree_code code, cp_expr xarg,
5393 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5394{
5395 tree orig_expr = xarg;
5396 tree exp;
5397 int ptrmem = 0;
5398 tree overload = NULL_TREE;
5399
5400 if (processing_template_decl)
5401 {
5402 if (type_dependent_expression_p (xarg))
5403 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, code, xarg.get_value (), NULL_TREE);
5404
5405 xarg = build_non_dependent_expr (xarg);
5406 }
5407
5408 exp = NULL_TREE;
5409
5410 /* [expr.unary.op] says:
5411
5412 The address of an object of incomplete type can be taken.
5413
5414 (And is just the ordinary address operator, not an overloaded
5415 "operator &".) However, if the type is a template
5416 specialization, we must complete the type at this point so that
5417 an overloaded "operator &" will be available if required. */
5418 if (code == ADDR_EXPR
5419 && TREE_CODE (xarg) != TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR
5420 && ((CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (xarg))
5421 && !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (TREE_TYPE (xarg))))
5422 || (TREE_CODE (xarg) == OFFSET_REF)))
5423 /* Don't look for a function. */;
5424 else
5425 exp = build_new_op (loc, code, LOOKUP_NORMAL, xarg, NULL_TREE,
5426 NULL_TREE, &overload, complain);
5427
5428 if (!exp && code == ADDR_EXPR)
5429 {
5430 if (is_overloaded_fn (xarg))
5431 {
5432 tree fn = get_first_fn (xarg);
5433 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (fn) || DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (fn))
5434 {
5435 if (complain & tf_error)
5436 error (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (fn)
5437 ? G_("taking address of constructor %qE")
5438 : G_("taking address of destructor %qE"),
5439 xarg.get_value ());
5440 return error_mark_node;
5441 }
5442 }
5443
5444 /* A pointer to member-function can be formed only by saying
5445 &X::mf. */
5446 if (!flag_ms_extensions && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (xarg)) == METHOD_TYPE
5447 && (TREE_CODE (xarg) != OFFSET_REF || !PTRMEM_OK_P (xarg)))
5448 {
5449 if (TREE_CODE (xarg) != OFFSET_REF
5450 || !TYPE_P (TREE_OPERAND (xarg, 0)))
5451 {
5452 if (complain & tf_error)
5453 {
5454 error ("invalid use of %qE to form a "
5455 "pointer-to-member-function", xarg.get_value ());
5456 if (TREE_CODE (xarg) != OFFSET_REF)
5457 inform (input_location, " a qualified-id is required");
5458 }
5459 return error_mark_node;
5460 }
5461 else
5462 {
5463 if (complain & tf_error)
5464 error ("parentheses around %qE cannot be used to form a"
5465 " pointer-to-member-function",
5466 xarg.get_value ());
5467 else
5468 return error_mark_node;
5469 PTRMEM_OK_P (xarg) = 1;
5470 }
5471 }
5472
5473 if (TREE_CODE (xarg) == OFFSET_REF)
5474 {
5475 ptrmem = PTRMEM_OK_P (xarg);
5476
5477 if (!ptrmem && !flag_ms_extensions
5478 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (xarg, 1))) == METHOD_TYPE)
5479 {
5480 /* A single non-static member, make sure we don't allow a
5481 pointer-to-member. */
5482 xarg = build2 (OFFSET_REF, TREE_TYPE (xarg),
5483 TREE_OPERAND (xarg, 0),
5484 ovl_cons (TREE_OPERAND (xarg, 1), NULL_TREE));
5485 PTRMEM_OK_P (xarg) = ptrmem;
5486 }
5487 }
5488
5489 exp = cp_build_addr_expr_strict (xarg, complain);
5490 }
5491
5492 if (processing_template_decl && exp != error_mark_node)
5493 {
5494 if (overload != NULL_TREE)
5495 return (build_min_non_dep_op_overload
5496 (code, exp, overload, orig_expr, integer_zero_node));
5497
5498 exp = build_min_non_dep (code, exp, orig_expr,
5499 /*For {PRE,POST}{INC,DEC}REMENT_EXPR*/NULL_TREE);
5500 }
5501 if (TREE_CODE (exp) == ADDR_EXPR)
5502 PTRMEM_OK_P (exp) = ptrmem;
5503 return exp;
5504}
5505
5506/* Construct and perhaps optimize a tree representation
5507 for __builtin_addressof operation. ARG specifies the operand. */
5508
5509tree
5510cp_build_addressof (location_t loc, tree arg, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5511{
5512 tree orig_expr = arg;
5513
5514 if (processing_template_decl)
5515 {
5516 if (type_dependent_expression_p (arg))
5517 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, ADDRESSOF_EXPR, arg, NULL_TREE);
5518
5519 arg = build_non_dependent_expr (arg);
5520 }
5521
5522 tree exp = cp_build_addr_expr_strict (arg, complain);
5523
5524 if (processing_template_decl && exp != error_mark_node)
5525 exp = build_min_non_dep (ADDRESSOF_EXPR, exp, orig_expr, NULL_TREE);
5526 return exp;
5527}
5528
5529/* Like c_common_truthvalue_conversion, but handle pointer-to-member
5530 constants, where a null value is represented by an INTEGER_CST of
5531 -1. */
5532
5533tree
5534cp_truthvalue_conversion (tree expr)
5535{
5536 tree type = TREE_TYPE (expr);
5537 if (TYPE_PTR_OR_PTRMEM_P (type)
5538 /* Avoid ICE on invalid use of non-static member function. */
5539 || TREE_CODE (expr) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5540 return build_binary_op (input_location, NE_EXPR, expr, nullptr_node, 1);
5541 else
5542 return c_common_truthvalue_conversion (input_location, expr);
5543}
5544
5545/* Just like cp_truthvalue_conversion, but we want a CLEANUP_POINT_EXPR. */
5546
5547tree
5548condition_conversion (tree expr)
5549{
5550 tree t;
5551 if (processing_template_decl)
5552 return expr;
5553 t = perform_implicit_conversion_flags (boolean_type_node, expr,
5554 tf_warning_or_error, LOOKUP_NORMAL);
5555 t = fold_build_cleanup_point_expr (boolean_type_node, t);
5556 return t;
5557}
5558
5559/* Returns the address of T. This function will fold away
5560 ADDR_EXPR of INDIRECT_REF. */
5561
5562tree
5563build_address (tree t)
5564{
5565 if (error_operand_p (t) || !cxx_mark_addressable (t))
5566 return error_mark_node;
5567 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CODE (t) != CONSTRUCTOR);
5568 t = build_fold_addr_expr (t);
5569 if (TREE_CODE (t) != ADDR_EXPR)
5570 t = rvalue (t);
5571 return t;
5572}
5573
5574/* Return a NOP_EXPR converting EXPR to TYPE. */
5575
5576tree
5577build_nop (tree type, tree expr)
5578{
5579 if (type == error_mark_node || error_operand_p (expr))
5580 return expr;
5581 return build1_loc (EXPR_LOCATION (expr), NOP_EXPR, type, expr);
5582}
5583
5584/* Take the address of ARG, whatever that means under C++ semantics.
5585 If STRICT_LVALUE is true, require an lvalue; otherwise, allow xvalues
5586 and class rvalues as well.
5587
5588 Nothing should call this function directly; instead, callers should use
5589 cp_build_addr_expr or cp_build_addr_expr_strict. */
5590
5591static tree
5592cp_build_addr_expr_1 (tree arg, bool strict_lvalue, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5593{
5594 tree argtype;
5595 tree val;
5596
5597 if (!arg || error_operand_p (arg))
5598 return error_mark_node;
5599
5600 arg = mark_lvalue_use (arg);
5601 argtype = lvalue_type (arg);
5602
5603 gcc_assert (!identifier_p (arg) || !IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (arg));
5604
5605 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == COMPONENT_REF && type_unknown_p (arg)
5606 && !really_overloaded_fn (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1)))
5607 {
5608 /* They're trying to take the address of a unique non-static
5609 member function. This is ill-formed (except in MS-land),
5610 but let's try to DTRT.
5611 Note: We only handle unique functions here because we don't
5612 want to complain if there's a static overload; non-unique
5613 cases will be handled by instantiate_type. But we need to
5614 handle this case here to allow casts on the resulting PMF.
5615 We could defer this in non-MS mode, but it's easier to give
5616 a useful error here. */
5617
5618 /* Inside constant member functions, the `this' pointer
5619 contains an extra const qualifier. TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT
5620 is used here to remove this const from the diagnostics
5621 and the created OFFSET_REF. */
5622 tree base = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0)));
5623 tree fn = get_first_fn (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1));
5624 if (!mark_used (fn, complain) && !(complain & tf_error))
5625 return error_mark_node;
5626
5627 if (! flag_ms_extensions)
5628 {
5629 tree name = DECL_NAME (fn);
5630 if (!(complain & tf_error))
5631 return error_mark_node;
5632 else if (current_class_type
5633 && TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0) == current_class_ref)
5634 /* An expression like &memfn. */
5635 permerror (input_location, "ISO C++ forbids taking the address of an unqualified"
5636 " or parenthesized non-static member function to form"
5637 " a pointer to member function. Say %<&%T::%D%>",
5638 base, name);
5639 else
5640 permerror (input_location, "ISO C++ forbids taking the address of a bound member"
5641 " function to form a pointer to member function."
5642 " Say %<&%T::%D%>",
5643 base, name);
5644 }
5645 arg = build_offset_ref (base, fn, /*address_p=*/true, complain);
5646 }
5647
5648 /* Uninstantiated types are all functions. Taking the
5649 address of a function is a no-op, so just return the
5650 argument. */
5651 if (type_unknown_p (arg))
5652 return build1 (ADDR_EXPR, unknown_type_node, arg);
5653
5654 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == OFFSET_REF)
5655 /* We want a pointer to member; bypass all the code for actually taking
5656 the address of something. */
5657 goto offset_ref;
5658
5659 /* Anything not already handled and not a true memory reference
5660 is an error. */
5661 if (TREE_CODE (argtype) != FUNCTION_TYPE
5662 && TREE_CODE (argtype) != METHOD_TYPE)
5663 {
5664 cp_lvalue_kind kind = lvalue_kind (arg);
5665 if (kind == clk_none)
5666 {
5667 if (complain & tf_error)
5668 lvalue_error (input_location, lv_addressof);
5669 return error_mark_node;
5670 }
5671 if (strict_lvalue && (kind & (clk_rvalueref|clk_class)))
5672 {
5673 if (!(complain & tf_error))
5674 return error_mark_node;
5675 if (kind & clk_class)
5676 /* Make this a permerror because we used to accept it. */
5677 permerror (input_location, "taking address of temporary");
5678 else
5679 error ("taking address of xvalue (rvalue reference)");
5680 }
5681 }
5682
5683 if (TREE_CODE (argtype) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
5684 {
5685 tree type = build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (argtype));
5686 arg = build1 (CONVERT_EXPR, type, arg);
5687 return arg;
5688 }
5689 else if (pedantic && DECL_MAIN_P (arg))
5690 {
5691 /* ARM $3.4 */
5692 /* Apparently a lot of autoconf scripts for C++ packages do this,
5693 so only complain if -Wpedantic. */
5694 if (complain & (flag_pedantic_errors ? tf_error : tf_warning))
5695 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpedantic,
5696 "ISO C++ forbids taking address of function %<::main%>");
5697 else if (flag_pedantic_errors)
5698 return error_mark_node;
5699 }
5700
5701 /* Let &* cancel out to simplify resulting code. */
5702 if (INDIRECT_REF_P (arg))
5703 {
5704 arg = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0);
5705 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg)) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
5706 {
5707 tree type = build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (arg)));
5708 arg = build1 (CONVERT_EXPR, type, arg);
5709 }
5710 else
5711 /* Don't let this be an lvalue. */
5712 arg = rvalue (arg);
5713 return arg;
5714 }
5715
5716 /* Handle complex lvalues (when permitted)
5717 by reduction to simpler cases. */
5718 val = unary_complex_lvalue (ADDR_EXPR, arg);
5719 if (val != 0)
5720 return val;
5721
5722 switch (TREE_CODE (arg))
5723 {
5724 CASE_CONVERT:
5725 case FLOAT_EXPR:
5726 case FIX_TRUNC_EXPR:
5727 /* We should have handled this above in the lvalue_kind check. */
5728 gcc_unreachable ();
5729 break;
5730
5731 case BASELINK:
5732 arg = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (arg);
5733 /* Fall through. */
5734
5735 case OVERLOAD:
5736 arg = OVL_CURRENT (arg);
5737 break;
5738
5739 case OFFSET_REF:
5740 offset_ref:
5741 /* Turn a reference to a non-static data member into a
5742 pointer-to-member. */
5743 {
5744 tree type;
5745 tree t;
5746
5747 gcc_assert (PTRMEM_OK_P (arg));
5748
5749 t = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1);
5750 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
5751 {
5752 if (complain & tf_error)
5753 error ("cannot create pointer to reference member %qD", t);
5754 return error_mark_node;
5755 }
5756
5757 type = build_ptrmem_type (context_for_name_lookup (t),
5758 TREE_TYPE (t));
5759 t = make_ptrmem_cst (type, TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1));
5760 return t;
5761 }
5762
5763 default:
5764 break;
5765 }
5766
5767 if (argtype != error_mark_node)
5768 argtype = build_pointer_type (argtype);
5769
5770 if (bitfield_p (arg))
5771 {
5772 if (complain & tf_error)
5773 error ("attempt to take address of bit-field");
5774 return error_mark_node;
5775 }
5776
5777 /* In a template, we are processing a non-dependent expression
5778 so we can just form an ADDR_EXPR with the correct type. */
5779 if (processing_template_decl || TREE_CODE (arg) != COMPONENT_REF)
5780 {
5781 val = build_address (arg);
5782 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == OFFSET_REF)
5783 PTRMEM_OK_P (val) = PTRMEM_OK_P (arg);
5784 }
5785 else if (BASELINK_P (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1)))
5786 {
5787 tree fn = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1));
5788
5789 /* We can only get here with a single static member
5790 function. */
5791 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL
5792 && DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (fn));
5793 if (!mark_used (fn, complain) && !(complain & tf_error))
5794 return error_mark_node;
5795 val = build_address (fn);
5796 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0)))
5797 /* Do not lose object's side effects. */
5798 val = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (val),
5799 TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0), val);
5800 }
5801 else
5802 {
5803 tree object = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0);
5804 tree field = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1);
5805 gcc_assert (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
5806 (TREE_TYPE (object), decl_type_context (field)));
5807 val = build_address (arg);
5808 }
5809
5810 if (TYPE_PTR_P (argtype)
5811 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (argtype)) == METHOD_TYPE)
5812 {
5813 build_ptrmemfunc_type (argtype);
5814 val = build_ptrmemfunc (argtype, val, 0,
5815 /*c_cast_p=*/false,
5816 complain);
5817 }
5818
5819 return val;
5820}
5821
5822/* Take the address of ARG if it has one, even if it's an rvalue. */
5823
5824tree
5825cp_build_addr_expr (tree arg, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5826{
5827 return cp_build_addr_expr_1 (arg, 0, complain);
5828}
5829
5830/* Take the address of ARG, but only if it's an lvalue. */
5831
5832static tree
5833cp_build_addr_expr_strict (tree arg, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5834{
5835 return cp_build_addr_expr_1 (arg, 1, complain);
5836}
5837
5838/* C++: Must handle pointers to members.
5839
5840 Perhaps type instantiation should be extended to handle conversion
5841 from aggregates to types we don't yet know we want? (Or are those
5842 cases typically errors which should be reported?)
5843
5844 NOCONVERT suppresses the default promotions (such as from short to int). */
5845
5846tree
5847cp_build_unary_op (enum tree_code code, tree xarg, bool noconvert,
5848 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5849{
5850 /* No default_conversion here. It causes trouble for ADDR_EXPR. */
5851 tree arg = xarg;
5852 location_t location = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (arg, input_location);
5853 tree argtype = 0;
5854 const char *errstring = NULL;
5855 tree val;
5856 const char *invalid_op_diag;
5857
5858 if (!arg || error_operand_p (arg))
5859 return error_mark_node;
5860
5861 if ((invalid_op_diag
5862 = targetm.invalid_unary_op ((code == UNARY_PLUS_EXPR
5863 ? CONVERT_EXPR
5864 : code),
5865 TREE_TYPE (xarg))))
5866 {
5867 if (complain & tf_error)
5868 error (invalid_op_diag);
5869 return error_mark_node;
5870 }
5871
5872 switch (code)
5873 {
5874 case UNARY_PLUS_EXPR:
5875 case NEGATE_EXPR:
5876 {
5877 int flags = WANT_ARITH | WANT_ENUM;
5878 /* Unary plus (but not unary minus) is allowed on pointers. */
5879 if (code == UNARY_PLUS_EXPR)
5880 flags |= WANT_POINTER;
5881 arg = build_expr_type_conversion (flags, arg, true);
5882 if (!arg)
5883 errstring = (code == NEGATE_EXPR
5884 ? _("wrong type argument to unary minus")
5885 : _("wrong type argument to unary plus"));
5886 else
5887 {
5888 if (!noconvert && CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
5889 arg = cp_perform_integral_promotions (arg, complain);
5890
5891 /* Make sure the result is not an lvalue: a unary plus or minus
5892 expression is always a rvalue. */
5893 arg = rvalue (arg);
5894 }
5895 }
5896 break;
5897
5898 case BIT_NOT_EXPR:
5899 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg)) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
5900 {
5901 code = CONJ_EXPR;
5902 if (!noconvert)
5903 {
5904 arg = cp_default_conversion (arg, complain);
5905 if (arg == error_mark_node)
5906 return error_mark_node;
5907 }
5908 }
5909 else if (!(arg = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_INT | WANT_ENUM
5910 | WANT_VECTOR_OR_COMPLEX,
5911 arg, true)))
5912 errstring = _("wrong type argument to bit-complement");
5913 else if (!noconvert && CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
5914 {
5915 /* Warn if the expression has boolean value. */
5916 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg)) == BOOLEAN_TYPE
5917 && (complain & tf_warning)
5918 && warning_at (location, OPT_Wbool_operation,
5919 "%<~%> on an expression of type bool"))
5920 inform (location, "did you mean to use logical not (%<!%>)?");
5921 arg = cp_perform_integral_promotions (arg, complain);
5922 }
5923 else if (!noconvert && VECTOR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
5924 arg = mark_rvalue_use (arg);
5925 break;
5926
5927 case ABS_EXPR:
5928 if (!(arg = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_ARITH | WANT_ENUM, arg, true)))
5929 errstring = _("wrong type argument to abs");
5930 else if (!noconvert)
5931 {
5932 arg = cp_default_conversion (arg, complain);
5933 if (arg == error_mark_node)
5934 return error_mark_node;
5935 }
5936 break;
5937
5938 case CONJ_EXPR:
5939 /* Conjugating a real value is a no-op, but allow it anyway. */
5940 if (!(arg = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_ARITH | WANT_ENUM, arg, true)))
5941 errstring = _("wrong type argument to conjugation");
5942 else if (!noconvert)
5943 {
5944 arg = cp_default_conversion (arg, complain);
5945 if (arg == error_mark_node)
5946 return error_mark_node;
5947 }
5948 break;
5949
5950 case TRUTH_NOT_EXPR:
5951 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
5952 return cp_build_binary_op (input_location, EQ_EXPR, arg,
5953 build_zero_cst (TREE_TYPE (arg)), complain);
5954 arg = perform_implicit_conversion (boolean_type_node, arg,
5955 complain);
5956 val = invert_truthvalue_loc (input_location, arg);
5957 if (arg != error_mark_node)
5958 return val;
5959 errstring = _("in argument to unary !");
5960 break;
5961
5962 case NOP_EXPR:
5963 break;
5964
5965 case REALPART_EXPR:
5966 case IMAGPART_EXPR:
5967 arg = build_real_imag_expr (input_location, code, arg);
5968 return arg;
5969
5970 case PREINCREMENT_EXPR:
5971 case POSTINCREMENT_EXPR:
5972 case PREDECREMENT_EXPR:
5973 case POSTDECREMENT_EXPR:
5974 /* Handle complex lvalues (when permitted)
5975 by reduction to simpler cases. */
5976
5977 val = unary_complex_lvalue (code, arg);
5978 if (val != 0)
5979 return val;
5980
5981 arg = mark_lvalue_use (arg);
5982
5983 /* Increment or decrement the real part of the value,
5984 and don't change the imaginary part. */
5985 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg)) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
5986 {
5987 tree real, imag;
5988
5989 arg = cp_stabilize_reference (arg);
5990 real = cp_build_unary_op (REALPART_EXPR, arg, true, complain);
5991 imag = cp_build_unary_op (IMAGPART_EXPR, arg, true, complain);
5992 real = cp_build_unary_op (code, real, true, complain);
5993 if (real == error_mark_node || imag == error_mark_node)
5994 return error_mark_node;
5995 return build2 (COMPLEX_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (arg),
5996 real, imag);
5997 }
5998
5999 /* Report invalid types. */
6000
6001 if (!(arg = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_ARITH | WANT_POINTER,
6002 arg, true)))
6003 {
6004 if (code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR)
6005 errstring = _("no pre-increment operator for type");
6006 else if (code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR)
6007 errstring = _("no post-increment operator for type");
6008 else if (code == PREDECREMENT_EXPR)
6009 errstring = _("no pre-decrement operator for type");
6010 else
6011 errstring = _("no post-decrement operator for type");
6012 break;
6013 }
6014 else if (arg == error_mark_node)
6015 return error_mark_node;
6016
6017 /* Report something read-only. */
6018
6019 if (CP_TYPE_CONST_P (TREE_TYPE (arg))
6020 || TREE_READONLY (arg))
6021 {
6022 if (complain & tf_error)
6023 cxx_readonly_error (arg, ((code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
6024 || code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR)
6025 ? lv_increment : lv_decrement));
6026 else
6027 return error_mark_node;
6028 }
6029
6030 {
6031 tree inc;
6032 tree declared_type = unlowered_expr_type (arg);
6033
6034 argtype = TREE_TYPE (arg);
6035
6036 /* ARM $5.2.5 last annotation says this should be forbidden. */
6037 if (TREE_CODE (argtype) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
6038 {
6039 if (complain & tf_error)
6040 permerror (input_location, (code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR || code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR)
6041 ? G_("ISO C++ forbids incrementing an enum")
6042 : G_("ISO C++ forbids decrementing an enum"));
6043 else
6044 return error_mark_node;
6045 }
6046
6047 /* Compute the increment. */
6048
6049 if (TYPE_PTR_P (argtype))
6050 {
6051 tree type = complete_type (TREE_TYPE (argtype));
6052
6053 if (!COMPLETE_OR_VOID_TYPE_P (type))
6054 {
6055 if (complain & tf_error)
6056 error (((code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
6057 || code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR))
6058 ? G_("cannot increment a pointer to incomplete type %qT")
6059 : G_("cannot decrement a pointer to incomplete type %qT"),
6060 TREE_TYPE (argtype));
6061 else
6062 return error_mark_node;
6063 }
6064 else if (!TYPE_PTROB_P (argtype))
6065 {
6066 if (complain & tf_error)
6067 pedwarn (input_location, OPT_Wpointer_arith,
6068 (code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
6069 || code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR)
6070 ? G_("ISO C++ forbids incrementing a pointer of type %qT")
6071 : G_("ISO C++ forbids decrementing a pointer of type %qT"),
6072 argtype);
6073 else
6074 return error_mark_node;
6075 }
6076
6077 inc = cxx_sizeof_nowarn (TREE_TYPE (argtype));
6078 }
6079 else
6080 inc = VECTOR_TYPE_P (argtype)
6081 ? build_one_cst (argtype)
6082 : integer_one_node;
6083
6084 inc = cp_convert (argtype, inc, complain);
6085
6086 /* If 'arg' is an Objective-C PROPERTY_REF expression, then we
6087 need to ask Objective-C to build the increment or decrement
6088 expression for it. */
6089 if (objc_is_property_ref (arg))
6090 return objc_build_incr_expr_for_property_ref (input_location, code,
6091 arg, inc);
6092
6093 /* Complain about anything else that is not a true lvalue. */
6094 if (!lvalue_or_else (arg, ((code == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
6095 || code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR)
6096 ? lv_increment : lv_decrement),
6097 complain))
6098 return error_mark_node;
6099
6100 /* Forbid using -- or ++ in C++17 on `bool'. */
6101 if (TREE_CODE (declared_type) == BOOLEAN_TYPE)
6102 {
6103 if (code == POSTDECREMENT_EXPR || code == PREDECREMENT_EXPR)
6104 {
6105 if (complain & tf_error)
6106 error ("use of an operand of type %qT in %<operator--%> "
6107 "is forbidden", boolean_type_node);
6108 return error_mark_node;
6109 }
6110 else
6111 {
6112 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z)
6113 {
6114 if (complain & tf_error)
6115 error ("use of an operand of type %qT in "
6116 "%<operator++%> is forbidden in C++1z",
6117 boolean_type_node);
6118 return error_mark_node;
6119 }
6120 /* Otherwise, [depr.incr.bool] says this is deprecated. */
6121 else if (!in_system_header_at (input_location))
6122 warning (OPT_Wdeprecated, "use of an operand of type %qT "
6123 "in %<operator++%> is deprecated",
6124 boolean_type_node);
6125 }
6126 val = boolean_increment (code, arg);
6127 }
6128 else if (code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR || code == POSTDECREMENT_EXPR)
6129 /* An rvalue has no cv-qualifiers. */
6130 val = build2 (code, cv_unqualified (TREE_TYPE (arg)), arg, inc);
6131 else
6132 val = build2 (code, TREE_TYPE (arg), arg, inc);
6133
6134 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (val) = 1;
6135 return val;
6136 }
6137
6138 case ADDR_EXPR:
6139 /* Note that this operation never does default_conversion
6140 regardless of NOCONVERT. */
6141 return cp_build_addr_expr (arg, complain);
6142
6143 default:
6144 break;
6145 }
6146
6147 if (!errstring)
6148 {
6149 if (argtype == 0)
6150 argtype = TREE_TYPE (arg);
6151 return build1 (code, argtype, arg);
6152 }
6153
6154 if (complain & tf_error)
6155 error ("%s", errstring);
6156 return error_mark_node;
6157}
6158
6159/* Hook for the c-common bits that build a unary op. */
6160tree
6161build_unary_op (location_t /*location*/,
6162 enum tree_code code, tree xarg, bool noconvert)
6163{
6164 return cp_build_unary_op (code, xarg, noconvert, tf_warning_or_error);
6165}
6166
6167/* Adjust LVALUE, an MODIFY_EXPR, PREINCREMENT_EXPR or PREDECREMENT_EXPR,
6168 so that it is a valid lvalue even for GENERIC by replacing
6169 (lhs = rhs) with ((lhs = rhs), lhs)
6170 (--lhs) with ((--lhs), lhs)
6171 (++lhs) with ((++lhs), lhs)
6172 and if lhs has side-effects, calling cp_stabilize_reference on it, so
6173 that it can be evaluated multiple times. */
6174
6175tree
6176genericize_compound_lvalue (tree lvalue)
6177{
6178 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (TREE_OPERAND (lvalue, 0)))
6179 lvalue = build2 (TREE_CODE (lvalue), TREE_TYPE (lvalue),
6180 cp_stabilize_reference (TREE_OPERAND (lvalue, 0)),
6181 TREE_OPERAND (lvalue, 1));
6182 return build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (lvalue, 0)),
6183 lvalue, TREE_OPERAND (lvalue, 0));
6184}
6185
6186/* Apply unary lvalue-demanding operator CODE to the expression ARG
6187 for certain kinds of expressions which are not really lvalues
6188 but which we can accept as lvalues.
6189
6190 If ARG is not a kind of expression we can handle, return
6191 NULL_TREE. */
6192
6193tree
6194unary_complex_lvalue (enum tree_code code, tree arg)
6195{
6196 /* Inside a template, making these kinds of adjustments is
6197 pointless; we are only concerned with the type of the
6198 expression. */
6199 if (processing_template_decl)
6200 return NULL_TREE;
6201
6202 /* Handle (a, b) used as an "lvalue". */
6203 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
6204 {
6205 tree real_result = cp_build_unary_op (code, TREE_OPERAND (arg, 1), false,
6206 tf_warning_or_error);
6207 return build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (real_result),
6208 TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0), real_result);
6209 }
6210
6211 /* Handle (a ? b : c) used as an "lvalue". */
6212 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == COND_EXPR
6213 || TREE_CODE (arg) == MIN_EXPR || TREE_CODE (arg) == MAX_EXPR)
6214 return rationalize_conditional_expr (code, arg, tf_warning_or_error);
6215
6216 /* Handle (a = b), (++a), and (--a) used as an "lvalue". */
6217 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == MODIFY_EXPR
6218 || TREE_CODE (arg) == PREINCREMENT_EXPR
6219 || TREE_CODE (arg) == PREDECREMENT_EXPR)
6220 return unary_complex_lvalue (code, genericize_compound_lvalue (arg));
6221
6222 if (code != ADDR_EXPR)
6223 return NULL_TREE;
6224
6225 /* Handle (a = b) used as an "lvalue" for `&'. */
6226 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == MODIFY_EXPR
6227 || TREE_CODE (arg) == INIT_EXPR)
6228 {
6229 tree real_result = cp_build_unary_op (code, TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0), false,
6230 tf_warning_or_error);
6231 arg = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (real_result),
6232 arg, real_result);
6233 TREE_NO_WARNING (arg) = 1;
6234 return arg;
6235 }
6236
6237 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg)) == FUNCTION_TYPE
6238 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg)) == METHOD_TYPE
6239 || TREE_CODE (arg) == OFFSET_REF)
6240 return NULL_TREE;
6241
6242 /* We permit compiler to make function calls returning
6243 objects of aggregate type look like lvalues. */
6244 {
6245 tree targ = arg;
6246
6247 if (TREE_CODE (targ) == SAVE_EXPR)
6248 targ = TREE_OPERAND (targ, 0);
6249
6250 if (TREE_CODE (targ) == CALL_EXPR && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (targ)))
6251 {
6252 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SAVE_EXPR)
6253 targ = arg;
6254 else
6255 targ = build_cplus_new (TREE_TYPE (arg), arg, tf_warning_or_error);
6256 return build1 (ADDR_EXPR, build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (arg)), targ);
6257 }
6258
6259 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SAVE_EXPR && INDIRECT_REF_P (targ))
6260 return build3 (SAVE_EXPR, build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (arg)),
6261 TREE_OPERAND (targ, 0), current_function_decl, NULL);
6262 }
6263
6264 /* Don't let anything else be handled specially. */
6265 return NULL_TREE;
6266}
6267
6268/* Mark EXP saying that we need to be able to take the
6269 address of it; it should not be allocated in a register.
6270 Value is true if successful. ARRAY_REF_P is true if this
6271 is for ARRAY_REF construction - in that case we don't want
6272 to look through VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR from VECTOR_TYPE to ARRAY_TYPE,
6273 it is fine to use ARRAY_REFs for vector subscripts on vector
6274 register variables.
6275
6276 C++: we do not allow `current_class_ptr' to be addressable. */
6277
6278bool
6279cxx_mark_addressable (tree exp, bool array_ref_p)
6280{
6281 tree x = exp;
6282
6283 while (1)
6284 switch (TREE_CODE (x))
6285 {
6286 case VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR:
6287 if (array_ref_p
6288 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (x)) == ARRAY_TYPE
6289 && VECTOR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (x, 0))))
6290 return true;
6291 /* FALLTHRU */
6292 case ADDR_EXPR:
6293 case COMPONENT_REF:
6294 case ARRAY_REF:
6295 case REALPART_EXPR:
6296 case IMAGPART_EXPR:
6297 x = TREE_OPERAND (x, 0);
6298 break;
6299
6300 case PARM_DECL:
6301 if (x == current_class_ptr)
6302 {
6303 error ("cannot take the address of %<this%>, which is an rvalue expression");
6304 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (x) = 1; /* so compiler doesn't die later. */
6305 return true;
6306 }
6307 /* Fall through. */
6308
6309 case VAR_DECL:
6310 /* Caller should not be trying to mark initialized
6311 constant fields addressable. */
6312 gcc_assert (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (x) == 0
6313 || DECL_IN_AGGR_P (x) == 0
6314 || TREE_STATIC (x)
6315 || DECL_EXTERNAL (x));
6316 /* Fall through. */
6317
6318 case RESULT_DECL:
6319 if (DECL_REGISTER (x) && !TREE_ADDRESSABLE (x)
6320 && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (x))
6321 {
6322 if (VAR_P (x) && DECL_HARD_REGISTER (x))
6323 {
6324 error
6325 ("address of explicit register variable %qD requested", x);
6326 return false;
6327 }
6328 else if (extra_warnings)
6329 warning
6330 (OPT_Wextra, "address requested for %qD, which is declared %<register%>", x);
6331 }
6332 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (x) = 1;
6333 return true;
6334
6335 case CONST_DECL:
6336 case FUNCTION_DECL:
6337 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (x) = 1;
6338 return true;
6339
6340 case CONSTRUCTOR:
6341 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (x) = 1;
6342 return true;
6343
6344 case TARGET_EXPR:
6345 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (x) = 1;
6346 cxx_mark_addressable (TREE_OPERAND (x, 0));
6347 return true;
6348
6349 default:
6350 return true;
6351 }
6352}
6353
6354/* Build and return a conditional expression IFEXP ? OP1 : OP2. */
6355
6356tree
6357build_x_conditional_expr (location_t loc, tree ifexp, tree op1, tree op2,
6358 tsubst_flags_t complain)
6359{
6360 tree orig_ifexp = ifexp;
6361 tree orig_op1 = op1;
6362 tree orig_op2 = op2;
6363 tree expr;
6364
6365 if (processing_template_decl)
6366 {
6367 /* The standard says that the expression is type-dependent if
6368 IFEXP is type-dependent, even though the eventual type of the
6369 expression doesn't dependent on IFEXP. */
6370 if (type_dependent_expression_p (ifexp)
6371 /* As a GNU extension, the middle operand may be omitted. */
6372 || (op1 && type_dependent_expression_p (op1))
6373 || type_dependent_expression_p (op2))
6374 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, COND_EXPR, ifexp, op1, op2);
6375 ifexp = build_non_dependent_expr (ifexp);
6376 if (op1)
6377 op1 = build_non_dependent_expr (op1);
6378 op2 = build_non_dependent_expr (op2);
6379 }
6380
6381 expr = build_conditional_expr (loc, ifexp, op1, op2, complain);
6382 if (processing_template_decl && expr != error_mark_node)
6383 {
6384 tree min = build_min_non_dep (COND_EXPR, expr,
6385 orig_ifexp, orig_op1, orig_op2);
6386 /* Remember that the result is an lvalue or xvalue. */
6387 if (glvalue_p (expr) && !glvalue_p (min))
6388 TREE_TYPE (min) = cp_build_reference_type (TREE_TYPE (min),
6389 !lvalue_p (expr));
6390 expr = convert_from_reference (min);
6391 }
6392 return expr;
6393}
6394
6395/* Given a list of expressions, return a compound expression
6396 that performs them all and returns the value of the last of them. */
6397
6398tree
6399build_x_compound_expr_from_list (tree list, expr_list_kind exp,
6400 tsubst_flags_t complain)
6401{
6402 tree expr = TREE_VALUE (list);
6403
6404 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr)
6405 && !CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (expr))
6406 {
6407 if (complain & tf_error)
6408 pedwarn (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (expr, input_location), 0,
6409 "list-initializer for non-class type must not "
6410 "be parenthesized");
6411 else
6412 return error_mark_node;
6413 }
6414
6415 if (TREE_CHAIN (list))
6416 {
6417 if (complain & tf_error)
6418 switch (exp)
6419 {
6420 case ELK_INIT:
6421 permerror (input_location, "expression list treated as compound "
6422 "expression in initializer");
6423 break;
6424 case ELK_MEM_INIT:
6425 permerror (input_location, "expression list treated as compound "
6426 "expression in mem-initializer");
6427 break;
6428 case ELK_FUNC_CAST:
6429 permerror (input_location, "expression list treated as compound "
6430 "expression in functional cast");
6431 break;
6432 default:
6433 gcc_unreachable ();
6434 }
6435 else
6436 return error_mark_node;
6437
6438 for (list = TREE_CHAIN (list); list; list = TREE_CHAIN (list))
6439 expr = build_x_compound_expr (EXPR_LOCATION (TREE_VALUE (list)),
6440 expr, TREE_VALUE (list), complain);
6441 }
6442
6443 return expr;
6444}
6445
6446/* Like build_x_compound_expr_from_list, but using a VEC. */
6447
6448tree
6449build_x_compound_expr_from_vec (vec<tree, va_gc> *vec, const char *msg,
6450 tsubst_flags_t complain)
6451{
6452 if (vec_safe_is_empty (vec))
6453 return NULL_TREE;
6454 else if (vec->length () == 1)
6455 return (*vec)[0];
6456 else
6457 {
6458 tree expr;
6459 unsigned int ix;
6460 tree t;
6461
6462 if (msg != NULL)
6463 {
6464 if (complain & tf_error)
6465 permerror (input_location,
6466 "%s expression list treated as compound expression",
6467 msg);
6468 else
6469 return error_mark_node;
6470 }
6471
6472 expr = (*vec)[0];
6473 for (ix = 1; vec->iterate (ix, &t); ++ix)
6474 expr = build_x_compound_expr (EXPR_LOCATION (t), expr,
6475 t, complain);
6476
6477 return expr;
6478 }
6479}
6480
6481/* Handle overloading of the ',' operator when needed. */
6482
6483tree
6484build_x_compound_expr (location_t loc, tree op1, tree op2,
6485 tsubst_flags_t complain)
6486{
6487 tree result;
6488 tree orig_op1 = op1;
6489 tree orig_op2 = op2;
6490 tree overload = NULL_TREE;
6491
6492 if (processing_template_decl)
6493 {
6494 if (type_dependent_expression_p (op1)
6495 || type_dependent_expression_p (op2))
6496 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, COMPOUND_EXPR, op1, op2);
6497 op1 = build_non_dependent_expr (op1);
6498 op2 = build_non_dependent_expr (op2);
6499 }
6500
6501 result = build_new_op (loc, COMPOUND_EXPR, LOOKUP_NORMAL, op1, op2,
6502 NULL_TREE, &overload, complain);
6503 if (!result)
6504 result = cp_build_compound_expr (op1, op2, complain);
6505
6506 if (processing_template_decl && result != error_mark_node)
6507 {
6508 if (overload != NULL_TREE)
6509 return (build_min_non_dep_op_overload
6510 (COMPOUND_EXPR, result, overload, orig_op1, orig_op2));
6511
6512 return build_min_non_dep (COMPOUND_EXPR, result, orig_op1, orig_op2);
6513 }
6514
6515 return result;
6516}
6517
6518/* Like cp_build_compound_expr, but for the c-common bits. */
6519
6520tree
6521build_compound_expr (location_t /*loc*/, tree lhs, tree rhs)
6522{
6523 return cp_build_compound_expr (lhs, rhs, tf_warning_or_error);
6524}
6525
6526/* Build a compound expression. */
6527
6528tree
6529cp_build_compound_expr (tree lhs, tree rhs, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6530{
6531 lhs = convert_to_void (lhs, ICV_LEFT_OF_COMMA, complain);
6532
6533 if (lhs == error_mark_node || rhs == error_mark_node)
6534 return error_mark_node;
6535
6536 if (flag_cilkplus
6537 && (TREE_CODE (lhs) == CILK_SPAWN_STMT
6538 || TREE_CODE (rhs) == CILK_SPAWN_STMT))
6539 {
6540 location_t loc = (EXPR_HAS_LOCATION (lhs) ? EXPR_LOCATION (lhs)
6541 : EXPR_LOCATION (rhs));
6542 error_at (loc,
6543 "spawned function call cannot be part of a comma expression");
6544 return error_mark_node;
6545 }
6546
6547 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == TARGET_EXPR)
6548 {
6549 /* If the rhs is a TARGET_EXPR, then build the compound
6550 expression inside the target_expr's initializer. This
6551 helps the compiler to eliminate unnecessary temporaries. */
6552 tree init = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 1);
6553
6554 init = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (init), lhs, init);
6555 TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 1) = init;
6556
6557 return rhs;
6558 }
6559
6560 if (type_unknown_p (rhs))
6561 {
6562 if (complain & tf_error)
6563 error ("no context to resolve type of %qE", rhs);
6564 return error_mark_node;
6565 }
6566
6567 return build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (rhs), lhs, rhs);
6568}
6569
6570/* Issue a diagnostic message if casting from SRC_TYPE to DEST_TYPE
6571 casts away constness. CAST gives the type of cast. Returns true
6572 if the cast is ill-formed, false if it is well-formed.
6573
6574 ??? This function warns for casting away any qualifier not just
6575 const. We would like to specify exactly what qualifiers are casted
6576 away.
6577*/
6578
6579static bool
6580check_for_casting_away_constness (tree src_type, tree dest_type,
6581 enum tree_code cast, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6582{
6583 /* C-style casts are allowed to cast away constness. With
6584 WARN_CAST_QUAL, we still want to issue a warning. */
6585 if (cast == CAST_EXPR && !warn_cast_qual)
6586 return false;
6587
6588 if (!casts_away_constness (src_type, dest_type, complain))
6589 return false;
6590
6591 switch (cast)
6592 {
6593 case CAST_EXPR:
6594 if (complain & tf_warning)
6595 warning (OPT_Wcast_qual,
6596 "cast from type %qT to type %qT casts away qualifiers",
6597 src_type, dest_type);
6598 return false;
6599
6600 case STATIC_CAST_EXPR:
6601 if (complain & tf_error)
6602 error ("static_cast from type %qT to type %qT casts away qualifiers",
6603 src_type, dest_type);
6604 return true;
6605
6606 case REINTERPRET_CAST_EXPR:
6607 if (complain & tf_error)
6608 error ("reinterpret_cast from type %qT to type %qT casts away qualifiers",
6609 src_type, dest_type);
6610 return true;
6611
6612 default:
6613 gcc_unreachable();
6614 }
6615}
6616
6617/*
6618 Warns if the cast from expression EXPR to type TYPE is useless.
6619 */
6620void
6621maybe_warn_about_useless_cast (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6622{
6623 if (warn_useless_cast
6624 && complain & tf_warning)
6625 {
6626 if ((TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE
6627 && (TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (type)
6628 ? xvalue_p (expr) : lvalue_p (expr))
6629 && same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (expr), TREE_TYPE (type)))
6630 || same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (expr), type))
6631 warning (OPT_Wuseless_cast, "useless cast to type %qT", type);
6632 }
6633}
6634
6635/* Convert EXPR (an expression with pointer-to-member type) to TYPE
6636 (another pointer-to-member type in the same hierarchy) and return
6637 the converted expression. If ALLOW_INVERSE_P is permitted, a
6638 pointer-to-derived may be converted to pointer-to-base; otherwise,
6639 only the other direction is permitted. If C_CAST_P is true, this
6640 conversion is taking place as part of a C-style cast. */
6641
6642tree
6643convert_ptrmem (tree type, tree expr, bool allow_inverse_p,
6644 bool c_cast_p, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6645{
6646 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (type))
6647 {
6648 tree delta;
6649
6650 if (TREE_CODE (expr) == PTRMEM_CST)
6651 expr = cplus_expand_constant (expr);
6652 delta = get_delta_difference (TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (expr)),
6653 TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (type),
6654 allow_inverse_p,
6655 c_cast_p, complain);
6656 if (delta == error_mark_node)
6657 return error_mark_node;
6658
6659 if (!integer_zerop (delta))
6660 {
6661 tree cond, op1, op2;
6662
6663 cond = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
6664 EQ_EXPR,
6665 expr,
6666 build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (expr), -1),
6667 complain);
6668 op1 = build_nop (ptrdiff_type_node, expr);
6669 op2 = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
6670 PLUS_EXPR, op1, delta,
6671 complain);
6672
6673 expr = fold_build3_loc (input_location,
6674 COND_EXPR, ptrdiff_type_node, cond, op1, op2);
6675
6676 }
6677
6678 return build_nop (type, expr);
6679 }
6680 else
6681 return build_ptrmemfunc (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (type), expr,
6682 allow_inverse_p, c_cast_p, complain);
6683}
6684
6685/* Perform a static_cast from EXPR to TYPE. When C_CAST_P is true,
6686 this static_cast is being attempted as one of the possible casts
6687 allowed by a C-style cast. (In that case, accessibility of base
6688 classes is not considered, and it is OK to cast away
6689 constness.) Return the result of the cast. *VALID_P is set to
6690 indicate whether or not the cast was valid. */
6691
6692static tree
6693build_static_cast_1 (tree type, tree expr, bool c_cast_p,
6694 bool *valid_p, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6695{
6696 tree intype;
6697 tree result;
6698 cp_lvalue_kind clk;
6699
6700 /* Assume the cast is valid. */
6701 *valid_p = true;
6702
6703 intype = unlowered_expr_type (expr);
6704
6705 /* Save casted types in the function's used types hash table. */
6706 used_types_insert (type);
6707
6708 /* [expr.static.cast]
6709
6710 An lvalue of type "cv1 B", where B is a class type, can be cast
6711 to type "reference to cv2 D", where D is a class derived (clause
6712 _class.derived_) from B, if a valid standard conversion from
6713 "pointer to D" to "pointer to B" exists (_conv.ptr_), cv2 is the
6714 same cv-qualification as, or greater cv-qualification than, cv1,
6715 and B is not a virtual base class of D. */
6716 /* We check this case before checking the validity of "TYPE t =
6717 EXPR;" below because for this case:
6718
6719 struct B {};
6720 struct D : public B { D(const B&); };
6721 extern B& b;
6722 void f() { static_cast<const D&>(b); }
6723
6724 we want to avoid constructing a new D. The standard is not
6725 completely clear about this issue, but our interpretation is
6726 consistent with other compilers. */
6727 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE
6728 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type))
6729 && CLASS_TYPE_P (intype)
6730 && (TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (type) || lvalue_p (expr))
6731 && DERIVED_FROM_P (intype, TREE_TYPE (type))
6732 && can_convert (build_pointer_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (intype)),
6733 build_pointer_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT
6734 (TREE_TYPE (type))),
6735 complain)
6736 && (c_cast_p
6737 || at_least_as_qualified_p (TREE_TYPE (type), intype)))
6738 {
6739 tree base;
6740
6741 /* There is a standard conversion from "D*" to "B*" even if "B"
6742 is ambiguous or inaccessible. If this is really a
6743 static_cast, then we check both for inaccessibility and
6744 ambiguity. However, if this is a static_cast being performed
6745 because the user wrote a C-style cast, then accessibility is
6746 not considered. */
6747 base = lookup_base (TREE_TYPE (type), intype,
6748 c_cast_p ? ba_unique : ba_check,
6749 NULL, complain);
6750 expr = build_address (expr);
6751
6752 if (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_VPTR)
6753 {
6754 tree ubsan_check
6755 = cp_ubsan_maybe_instrument_downcast (input_location, type,
6756 intype, expr);
6757 if (ubsan_check)
6758 expr = ubsan_check;
6759 }
6760
6761 /* Convert from "B*" to "D*". This function will check that "B"
6762 is not a virtual base of "D". */
6763 expr = build_base_path (MINUS_EXPR, expr, base, /*nonnull=*/false,
6764 complain);
6765
6766 /* Convert the pointer to a reference -- but then remember that
6767 there are no expressions with reference type in C++.
6768
6769 We call rvalue so that there's an actual tree code
6770 (NON_LVALUE_EXPR) for the static_cast; otherwise, if the operand
6771 is a variable with the same type, the conversion would get folded
6772 away, leaving just the variable and causing lvalue_kind to give
6773 the wrong answer. */
6774 return convert_from_reference (rvalue (cp_fold_convert (type, expr)));
6775 }
6776
6777 /* "A glvalue of type cv1 T1 can be cast to type rvalue reference to
6778 cv2 T2 if cv2 T2 is reference-compatible with cv1 T1 (8.5.3)." */
6779 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE
6780 && TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (type)
6781 && (clk = real_lvalue_p (expr))
6782 && reference_related_p (TREE_TYPE (type), intype)
6783 && (c_cast_p || at_least_as_qualified_p (TREE_TYPE (type), intype)))
6784 {
6785 if (clk == clk_ordinary)
6786 {
6787 /* Handle the (non-bit-field) lvalue case here by casting to
6788 lvalue reference and then changing it to an rvalue reference.
6789 Casting an xvalue to rvalue reference will be handled by the
6790 main code path. */
6791 tree lref = cp_build_reference_type (TREE_TYPE (type), false);
6792 result = (perform_direct_initialization_if_possible
6793 (lref, expr, c_cast_p, complain));
6794 result = build1 (NON_LVALUE_EXPR, type, result);
6795 return convert_from_reference (result);
6796 }
6797 else
6798 /* For a bit-field or packed field, bind to a temporary. */
6799 expr = rvalue (expr);
6800 }
6801
6802 /* Resolve overloaded address here rather than once in
6803 implicit_conversion and again in the inverse code below. */
6804 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type) && type_unknown_p (expr))
6805 {
6806 expr = instantiate_type (type, expr, complain);
6807 intype = TREE_TYPE (expr);
6808 }
6809
6810 /* [expr.static.cast]
6811
6812 Any expression can be explicitly converted to type cv void. */
6813 if (VOID_TYPE_P (type))
6814 return convert_to_void (expr, ICV_CAST, complain);
6815
6816 /* [class.abstract]
6817 An abstract class shall not be used ... as the type of an explicit
6818 conversion. */
6819 if (abstract_virtuals_error_sfinae (ACU_CAST, type, complain))
6820 return error_mark_node;
6821
6822 /* [expr.static.cast]
6823
6824 An expression e can be explicitly converted to a type T using a
6825 static_cast of the form static_cast<T>(e) if the declaration T
6826 t(e);" is well-formed, for some invented temporary variable
6827 t. */
6828 result = perform_direct_initialization_if_possible (type, expr,
6829 c_cast_p, complain);
6830 if (result)
6831 {
6832 result = convert_from_reference (result);
6833
6834 /* [expr.static.cast]
6835
6836 If T is a reference type, the result is an lvalue; otherwise,
6837 the result is an rvalue. */
6838 if (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE)
6839 {
6840 result = rvalue (result);
6841
6842 if (result == expr && SCALAR_TYPE_P (type))
6843 /* Leave some record of the cast. */
6844 result = build_nop (type, expr);
6845 }
6846 return result;
6847 }
6848
6849 /* [expr.static.cast]
6850
6851 The inverse of any standard conversion sequence (clause _conv_),
6852 other than the lvalue-to-rvalue (_conv.lval_), array-to-pointer
6853 (_conv.array_), function-to-pointer (_conv.func_), and boolean
6854 (_conv.bool_) conversions, can be performed explicitly using
6855 static_cast subject to the restriction that the explicit
6856 conversion does not cast away constness (_expr.const.cast_), and
6857 the following additional rules for specific cases: */
6858 /* For reference, the conversions not excluded are: integral
6859 promotions, floating point promotion, integral conversions,
6860 floating point conversions, floating-integral conversions,
6861 pointer conversions, and pointer to member conversions. */
6862 /* DR 128
6863
6864 A value of integral _or enumeration_ type can be explicitly
6865 converted to an enumeration type. */
6866 /* The effect of all that is that any conversion between any two
6867 types which are integral, floating, or enumeration types can be
6868 performed. */
6869 if ((INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type)
6870 || SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (type))
6871 && (INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (intype)
6872 || SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (intype)))
6873 return ocp_convert (type, expr, CONV_C_CAST, LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain);
6874
6875 if (TYPE_PTR_P (type) && TYPE_PTR_P (intype)
6876 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type))
6877 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (intype))
6878 && can_convert (build_pointer_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT
6879 (TREE_TYPE (intype))),
6880 build_pointer_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT
6881 (TREE_TYPE (type))),
6882 complain))
6883 {
6884 tree base;
6885
6886 if (!c_cast_p
6887 && check_for_casting_away_constness (intype, type, STATIC_CAST_EXPR,
6888 complain))
6889 return error_mark_node;
6890 base = lookup_base (TREE_TYPE (type), TREE_TYPE (intype),
6891 c_cast_p ? ba_unique : ba_check,
6892 NULL, complain);
6893 expr = build_base_path (MINUS_EXPR, expr, base, /*nonnull=*/false,
6894 complain);
6895
6896 if (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_VPTR)
6897 {
6898 tree ubsan_check
6899 = cp_ubsan_maybe_instrument_downcast (input_location, type,
6900 intype, expr);
6901 if (ubsan_check)
6902 expr = ubsan_check;
6903 }
6904
6905 return cp_fold_convert (type, expr);
6906 }
6907
6908 if ((TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (type) && TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (intype))
6909 || (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type) && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (intype)))
6910 {
6911 tree c1;
6912 tree c2;
6913 tree t1;
6914 tree t2;
6915
6916 c1 = TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (intype);
6917 c2 = TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (type);
6918
6919 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (type))
6920 {
6921 t1 = (build_ptrmem_type
6922 (c1,
6923 TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (intype))));
6924 t2 = (build_ptrmem_type
6925 (c2,
6926 TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (type))));
6927 }
6928 else
6929 {
6930 t1 = intype;
6931 t2 = type;
6932 }
6933 if (can_convert (t1, t2, complain) || can_convert (t2, t1, complain))
6934 {
6935 if (!c_cast_p
6936 && check_for_casting_away_constness (intype, type,
6937 STATIC_CAST_EXPR,
6938 complain))
6939 return error_mark_node;
6940 return convert_ptrmem (type, expr, /*allow_inverse_p=*/1,
6941 c_cast_p, complain);
6942 }
6943 }
6944
6945 /* [expr.static.cast]
6946
6947 An rvalue of type "pointer to cv void" can be explicitly
6948 converted to a pointer to object type. A value of type pointer
6949 to object converted to "pointer to cv void" and back to the
6950 original pointer type will have its original value. */
6951 if (TYPE_PTR_P (intype)
6952 && VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (intype))
6953 && TYPE_PTROB_P (type))
6954 {
6955 if (!c_cast_p
6956 && check_for_casting_away_constness (intype, type, STATIC_CAST_EXPR,
6957 complain))
6958 return error_mark_node;
6959 return build_nop (type, expr);
6960 }
6961
6962 *valid_p = false;
6963 return error_mark_node;
6964}
6965
6966/* Return an expression representing static_cast<TYPE>(EXPR). */
6967
6968tree
6969build_static_cast (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6970{
6971 tree result;
6972 bool valid_p;
6973
6974 if (type == error_mark_node || expr == error_mark_node)
6975 return error_mark_node;
6976
6977 if (processing_template_decl)
6978 {
6979 expr = build_min (STATIC_CAST_EXPR, type, expr);
6980 /* We don't know if it will or will not have side effects. */
6981 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (expr) = 1;
6982 return convert_from_reference (expr);
6983 }
6984
6985 /* build_c_cast puts on a NOP_EXPR to make the result not an lvalue.
6986 Strip such NOP_EXPRs if VALUE is being used in non-lvalue context. */
6987 if (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE
6988 && TREE_CODE (expr) == NOP_EXPR
6989 && TREE_TYPE (expr) == TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)))
6990 expr = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
6991
6992 result = build_static_cast_1 (type, expr, /*c_cast_p=*/false, &valid_p,
6993 complain);
6994 if (valid_p)
6995 {
6996 if (result != error_mark_node)
6997 maybe_warn_about_useless_cast (type, expr, complain);
6998 return result;
6999 }
7000
7001 if (complain & tf_error)
7002 error ("invalid static_cast from type %qT to type %qT",
7003 TREE_TYPE (expr), type);
7004 return error_mark_node;
7005}
7006
7007/* EXPR is an expression with member function or pointer-to-member
7008 function type. TYPE is a pointer type. Converting EXPR to TYPE is
7009 not permitted by ISO C++, but we accept it in some modes. If we
7010 are not in one of those modes, issue a diagnostic. Return the
7011 converted expression. */
7012
7013tree
7014convert_member_func_to_ptr (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7015{
7016 tree intype;
7017 tree decl;
7018
7019 intype = TREE_TYPE (expr);
7020 gcc_assert (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (intype)
7021 || TREE_CODE (intype) == METHOD_TYPE);
7022
7023 if (!(complain & tf_warning_or_error))
7024 return error_mark_node;
7025
7026 if (pedantic || warn_pmf2ptr)
7027 pedwarn (input_location, pedantic ? OPT_Wpedantic : OPT_Wpmf_conversions,
7028 "converting from %qT to %qT", intype, type);
7029
7030 if (TREE_CODE (intype) == METHOD_TYPE)
7031 expr = build_addr_func (expr, complain);
7032 else if (TREE_CODE (expr) == PTRMEM_CST)
7033 expr = build_address (PTRMEM_CST_MEMBER (expr));
7034 else
7035 {
7036 decl = maybe_dummy_object (TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (intype), 0);
7037 decl = build_address (decl);
7038 expr = get_member_function_from_ptrfunc (&decl, expr, complain);
7039 }
7040
7041 if (expr == error_mark_node)
7042 return error_mark_node;
7043
7044 return build_nop (type, expr);
7045}
7046
7047/* Return a representation for a reinterpret_cast from EXPR to TYPE.
7048 If C_CAST_P is true, this reinterpret cast is being done as part of
7049 a C-style cast. If VALID_P is non-NULL, *VALID_P is set to
7050 indicate whether or not reinterpret_cast was valid. */
7051
7052static tree
7053build_reinterpret_cast_1 (tree type, tree expr, bool c_cast_p,
7054 bool *valid_p, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7055{
7056 tree intype;
7057
7058 /* Assume the cast is invalid. */
7059 if (valid_p)
7060 *valid_p = true;
7061
7062 if (type == error_mark_node || error_operand_p (expr))
7063 return error_mark_node;
7064
7065 intype = TREE_TYPE (expr);
7066
7067 /* Save casted types in the function's used types hash table. */
7068 used_types_insert (type);
7069
7070 /* [expr.reinterpret.cast]
7071 An lvalue expression of type T1 can be cast to the type
7072 "reference to T2" if an expression of type "pointer to T1" can be
7073 explicitly converted to the type "pointer to T2" using a
7074 reinterpret_cast. */
7075 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7076 {
7077 if (! lvalue_p (expr))
7078 {
7079 if (complain & tf_error)
7080 error ("invalid cast of an rvalue expression of type "
7081 "%qT to type %qT",
7082 intype, type);
7083 return error_mark_node;
7084 }
7085
7086 /* Warn about a reinterpret_cast from "A*" to "B&" if "A" and
7087 "B" are related class types; the reinterpret_cast does not
7088 adjust the pointer. */
7089 if (TYPE_PTR_P (intype)
7090 && (complain & tf_warning)
7091 && (comptypes (TREE_TYPE (intype), TREE_TYPE (type),
7092 COMPARE_BASE | COMPARE_DERIVED)))
7093 warning (0, "casting %qT to %qT does not dereference pointer",
7094 intype, type);
7095
7096 expr = cp_build_addr_expr (expr, complain);
7097
7098 if (warn_strict_aliasing > 2)
7099 strict_aliasing_warning (TREE_TYPE (expr), type, expr);
7100
7101 if (expr != error_mark_node)
7102 expr = build_reinterpret_cast_1
7103 (build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (type)), expr, c_cast_p,
7104 valid_p, complain);
7105 if (expr != error_mark_node)
7106 /* cp_build_indirect_ref isn't right for rvalue refs. */
7107 expr = convert_from_reference (fold_convert (type, expr));
7108 return expr;
7109 }
7110
7111 /* As a G++ extension, we consider conversions from member
7112 functions, and pointers to member functions to
7113 pointer-to-function and pointer-to-void types. If
7114 -Wno-pmf-conversions has not been specified,
7115 convert_member_func_to_ptr will issue an error message. */
7116 if ((TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (intype)
7117 || TREE_CODE (intype) == METHOD_TYPE)
7118 && TYPE_PTR_P (type)
7119 && (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (type)) == FUNCTION_TYPE
7120 || VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type))))
7121 return convert_member_func_to_ptr (type, expr, complain);
7122
7123 /* If the cast is not to a reference type, the lvalue-to-rvalue,
7124 array-to-pointer, and function-to-pointer conversions are
7125 performed. */
7126 expr = decay_conversion (expr, complain);
7127
7128 /* build_c_cast puts on a NOP_EXPR to make the result not an lvalue.
7129 Strip such NOP_EXPRs if VALUE is being used in non-lvalue context. */
7130 if (TREE_CODE (expr) == NOP_EXPR
7131 && TREE_TYPE (expr) == TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)))
7132 expr = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
7133
7134 if (error_operand_p (expr))
7135 return error_mark_node;
7136
7137 intype = TREE_TYPE (expr);
7138
7139 /* [expr.reinterpret.cast]
7140 A pointer can be converted to any integral type large enough to
7141 hold it. ... A value of type std::nullptr_t can be converted to
7142 an integral type; the conversion has the same meaning and
7143 validity as a conversion of (void*)0 to the integral type. */
7144 if (CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (type)
7145 && (TYPE_PTR_P (intype) || NULLPTR_TYPE_P (intype)))
7146 {
7147 if (TYPE_PRECISION (type) < TYPE_PRECISION (intype))
7148 {
7149 if (complain & tf_error)
7150 permerror (input_location, "cast from %qT to %qT loses precision",
7151 intype, type);
7152 else
7153 return error_mark_node;
7154 }
7155 if (NULLPTR_TYPE_P (intype))
7156 return build_int_cst (type, 0);
7157 }
7158 /* [expr.reinterpret.cast]
7159 A value of integral or enumeration type can be explicitly
7160 converted to a pointer. */
7161 else if (TYPE_PTR_P (type) && INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (intype))
7162 /* OK */
7163 ;
7164 else if ((INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type)
7165 || TYPE_PTR_OR_PTRMEM_P (type))
7166 && same_type_p (type, intype))
7167 /* DR 799 */
7168 return rvalue (expr);
7169 else if ((TYPE_PTRFN_P (type) && TYPE_PTRFN_P (intype))
7170 || (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type) && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (intype)))
7171 return build_nop (type, expr);
7172 else if ((TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (type) && TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (intype))
7173 || (TYPE_PTROBV_P (type) && TYPE_PTROBV_P (intype)))
7174 {
7175 tree sexpr = expr;
7176
7177 if (!c_cast_p
7178 && check_for_casting_away_constness (intype, type,
7179 REINTERPRET_CAST_EXPR,
7180 complain))
7181 return error_mark_node;
7182 /* Warn about possible alignment problems. */
7183 if (STRICT_ALIGNMENT && warn_cast_align
7184 && (complain & tf_warning)
7185 && !VOID_TYPE_P (type)
7186 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (intype)) != FUNCTION_TYPE
7187 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type))
7188 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (intype))
7189 && TYPE_ALIGN (TREE_TYPE (type)) > TYPE_ALIGN (TREE_TYPE (intype)))
7190 warning (OPT_Wcast_align, "cast from %qT to %qT "
7191 "increases required alignment of target type", intype, type);
7192
7193 /* We need to strip nops here, because the front end likes to
7194 create (int *)&a for array-to-pointer decay, instead of &a[0]. */
7195 STRIP_NOPS (sexpr);
7196 if (warn_strict_aliasing <= 2)
7197 strict_aliasing_warning (intype, type, sexpr);
7198
7199 return build_nop (type, expr);
7200 }
7201 else if ((TYPE_PTRFN_P (type) && TYPE_PTROBV_P (intype))
7202 || (TYPE_PTRFN_P (intype) && TYPE_PTROBV_P (type)))
7203 {
7204 if (complain & tf_warning)
7205 /* C++11 5.2.10 p8 says that "Converting a function pointer to an
7206 object pointer type or vice versa is conditionally-supported." */
7207 warning (OPT_Wconditionally_supported,
7208 "casting between pointer-to-function and pointer-to-object "
7209 "is conditionally-supported");
7210 return build_nop (type, expr);
7211 }
7212 else if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
7213 return convert_to_vector (type, expr);
7214 else if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (intype)
7215 && INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type))
7216 return convert_to_integer_nofold (type, expr);
7217 else
7218 {
7219 if (valid_p)
7220 *valid_p = false;
7221 if (complain & tf_error)
7222 error ("invalid cast from type %qT to type %qT", intype, type);
7223 return error_mark_node;
7224 }
7225
7226 return cp_convert (type, expr, complain);
7227}
7228
7229tree
7230build_reinterpret_cast (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7231{
7232 tree r;
7233
7234 if (type == error_mark_node || expr == error_mark_node)
7235 return error_mark_node;
7236
7237 if (processing_template_decl)
7238 {
7239 tree t = build_min (REINTERPRET_CAST_EXPR, type, expr);
7240
7241 if (!TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t)
7242 && type_dependent_expression_p (expr))
7243 /* There might turn out to be side effects inside expr. */
7244 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t) = 1;
7245 return convert_from_reference (t);
7246 }
7247
7248 r = build_reinterpret_cast_1 (type, expr, /*c_cast_p=*/false,
7249 /*valid_p=*/NULL, complain);
7250 if (r != error_mark_node)
7251 maybe_warn_about_useless_cast (type, expr, complain);
7252 return r;
7253}
7254
7255/* Perform a const_cast from EXPR to TYPE. If the cast is valid,
7256 return an appropriate expression. Otherwise, return
7257 error_mark_node. If the cast is not valid, and COMPLAIN is true,
7258 then a diagnostic will be issued. If VALID_P is non-NULL, we are
7259 performing a C-style cast, its value upon return will indicate
7260 whether or not the conversion succeeded. */
7261
7262static tree
7263build_const_cast_1 (tree dst_type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain,
7264 bool *valid_p)
7265{
7266 tree src_type;
7267 tree reference_type;
7268
7269 /* Callers are responsible for handling error_mark_node as a
7270 destination type. */
7271 gcc_assert (dst_type != error_mark_node);
7272 /* In a template, callers should be building syntactic
7273 representations of casts, not using this machinery. */
7274 gcc_assert (!processing_template_decl);
7275
7276 /* Assume the conversion is invalid. */
7277 if (valid_p)
7278 *valid_p = false;
7279
7280 if (!POINTER_TYPE_P (dst_type) && !TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (dst_type))
7281 {
7282 if (complain & tf_error)
7283 error ("invalid use of const_cast with type %qT, "
7284 "which is not a pointer, "
7285 "reference, nor a pointer-to-data-member type", dst_type);
7286 return error_mark_node;
7287 }
7288
7289 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (dst_type)) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
7290 {
7291 if (complain & tf_error)
7292 error ("invalid use of const_cast with type %qT, which is a pointer "
7293 "or reference to a function type", dst_type);
7294 return error_mark_node;
7295 }
7296
7297 /* Save casted types in the function's used types hash table. */
7298 used_types_insert (dst_type);
7299
7300 src_type = TREE_TYPE (expr);
7301 /* Expressions do not really have reference types. */
7302 if (TREE_CODE (src_type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7303 src_type = TREE_TYPE (src_type);
7304
7305 /* [expr.const.cast]
7306
7307 For two object types T1 and T2, if a pointer to T1 can be explicitly
7308 converted to the type "pointer to T2" using a const_cast, then the
7309 following conversions can also be made:
7310
7311 -- an lvalue of type T1 can be explicitly converted to an lvalue of
7312 type T2 using the cast const_cast<T2&>;
7313
7314 -- a glvalue of type T1 can be explicitly converted to an xvalue of
7315 type T2 using the cast const_cast<T2&&>; and
7316
7317 -- if T1 is a class type, a prvalue of type T1 can be explicitly
7318 converted to an xvalue of type T2 using the cast const_cast<T2&&>. */
7319
7320 if (TREE_CODE (dst_type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7321 {
7322 reference_type = dst_type;
7323 if (!TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (dst_type)
7324 ? lvalue_p (expr)
7325 : obvalue_p (expr))
7326 /* OK. */;
7327 else
7328 {
7329 if (complain & tf_error)
7330 error ("invalid const_cast of an rvalue of type %qT to type %qT",
7331 src_type, dst_type);
7332 return error_mark_node;
7333 }
7334 dst_type = build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (dst_type));
7335 src_type = build_pointer_type (src_type);
7336 }
7337 else
7338 {
7339 reference_type = NULL_TREE;
7340 /* If the destination type is not a reference type, the
7341 lvalue-to-rvalue, array-to-pointer, and function-to-pointer
7342 conversions are performed. */
7343 src_type = type_decays_to (src_type);
7344 if (src_type == error_mark_node)
7345 return error_mark_node;
7346 }
7347
7348 if (TYPE_PTR_P (src_type) || TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (src_type))
7349 {
7350 if (comp_ptr_ttypes_const (dst_type, src_type))
7351 {
7352 if (valid_p)
7353 {
7354 *valid_p = true;
7355 /* This cast is actually a C-style cast. Issue a warning if
7356 the user is making a potentially unsafe cast. */
7357 check_for_casting_away_constness (src_type, dst_type,
7358 CAST_EXPR, complain);
7359 }
7360 if (reference_type)
7361 {
7362 expr = cp_build_addr_expr (expr, complain);
7363 if (expr == error_mark_node)
7364 return error_mark_node;
7365 expr = build_nop (reference_type, expr);
7366 return convert_from_reference (expr);
7367 }
7368 else
7369 {
7370 expr = decay_conversion (expr, complain);
7371 if (expr == error_mark_node)
7372 return error_mark_node;
7373
7374 /* build_c_cast puts on a NOP_EXPR to make the result not an
7375 lvalue. Strip such NOP_EXPRs if VALUE is being used in
7376 non-lvalue context. */
7377 if (TREE_CODE (expr) == NOP_EXPR
7378 && TREE_TYPE (expr) == TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)))
7379 expr = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
7380 return build_nop (dst_type, expr);
7381 }
7382 }
7383 else if (valid_p
7384 && !at_least_as_qualified_p (TREE_TYPE (dst_type),
7385 TREE_TYPE (src_type)))
7386 check_for_casting_away_constness (src_type, dst_type, CAST_EXPR,
7387 complain);
7388 }
7389
7390 if (complain & tf_error)
7391 error ("invalid const_cast from type %qT to type %qT",
7392 src_type, dst_type);
7393 return error_mark_node;
7394}
7395
7396tree
7397build_const_cast (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7398{
7399 tree r;
7400
7401 if (type == error_mark_node || error_operand_p (expr))
7402 return error_mark_node;
7403
7404 if (processing_template_decl)
7405 {
7406 tree t = build_min (CONST_CAST_EXPR, type, expr);
7407
7408 if (!TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t)
7409 && type_dependent_expression_p (expr))
7410 /* There might turn out to be side effects inside expr. */
7411 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t) = 1;
7412 return convert_from_reference (t);
7413 }
7414
7415 r = build_const_cast_1 (type, expr, complain, /*valid_p=*/NULL);
7416 if (r != error_mark_node)
7417 maybe_warn_about_useless_cast (type, expr, complain);
7418 return r;
7419}
7420
7421/* Like cp_build_c_cast, but for the c-common bits. */
7422
7423tree
7424build_c_cast (location_t /*loc*/, tree type, tree expr)
7425{
7426 return cp_build_c_cast (type, expr, tf_warning_or_error);
7427}
7428
7429/* Like the "build_c_cast" used for c-common, but using cp_expr to
7430 preserve location information even for tree nodes that don't
7431 support it. */
7432
7433cp_expr
7434build_c_cast (location_t loc, tree type, cp_expr expr)
7435{
7436 cp_expr result = cp_build_c_cast (type, expr, tf_warning_or_error);
7437 result.set_location (loc);
7438 return result;
7439}
7440
7441/* Build an expression representing an explicit C-style cast to type
7442 TYPE of expression EXPR. */
7443
7444tree
7445cp_build_c_cast (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7446{
7447 tree value = expr;
7448 tree result;
7449 bool valid_p;
7450
7451 if (type == error_mark_node || error_operand_p (expr))
7452 return error_mark_node;
7453
7454 if (processing_template_decl)
7455 {
7456 tree t = build_min (CAST_EXPR, type,
7457 tree_cons (NULL_TREE, value, NULL_TREE));
7458 /* We don't know if it will or will not have side effects. */
7459 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t) = 1;
7460 return convert_from_reference (t);
7461 }
7462
7463 /* Casts to a (pointer to a) specific ObjC class (or 'id' or
7464 'Class') should always be retained, because this information aids
7465 in method lookup. */
7466 if (objc_is_object_ptr (type)
7467 && objc_is_object_ptr (TREE_TYPE (expr)))
7468 return build_nop (type, expr);
7469
7470 /* build_c_cast puts on a NOP_EXPR to make the result not an lvalue.
7471 Strip such NOP_EXPRs if VALUE is being used in non-lvalue context. */
7472 if (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE
7473 && TREE_CODE (value) == NOP_EXPR
7474 && TREE_TYPE (value) == TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (value, 0)))
7475 value = TREE_OPERAND (value, 0);
7476
7477 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
7478 {
7479 /* Allow casting from T1* to T2[] because Cfront allows it.
7480 NIHCL uses it. It is not valid ISO C++ however. */
7481 if (TYPE_PTR_P (TREE_TYPE (expr)))
7482 {
7483 if (complain & tf_error)
7484 permerror (input_location, "ISO C++ forbids casting to an array type %qT", type);
7485 else
7486 return error_mark_node;
7487 type = build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
7488 }
7489 else
7490 {
7491 if (complain & tf_error)
7492 error ("ISO C++ forbids casting to an array type %qT", type);
7493 return error_mark_node;
7494 }
7495 }
7496
7497 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
7498 || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
7499 {
7500 if (complain & tf_error)
7501 error ("invalid cast to function type %qT", type);
