7502 return error_mark_node;
7503 }
7504
7505 if (TYPE_PTR_P (type)
7506 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (value)) == INTEGER_TYPE
7507 /* Casting to an integer of smaller size is an error detected elsewhere. */
7508 && TYPE_PRECISION (type) > TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (value))
7509 /* Don't warn about converting any constant. */
7510 && !TREE_CONSTANT (value))
7511 warning_at (input_location, OPT_Wint_to_pointer_cast,
7512 "cast to pointer from integer of different size");
7513
7514 /* A C-style cast can be a const_cast. */
7515 result = build_const_cast_1 (type, value, complain & tf_warning,
7516 &valid_p);
7517 if (valid_p)
7518 {
7519 if (result != error_mark_node)
7520 maybe_warn_about_useless_cast (type, value, complain);
7521 return result;
7522 }
7523
7524 /* Or a static cast. */
7525 result = build_static_cast_1 (type, value, /*c_cast_p=*/true,
7526 &valid_p, complain);
7527 /* Or a reinterpret_cast. */
7528 if (!valid_p)
7529 result = build_reinterpret_cast_1 (type, value, /*c_cast_p=*/true,
7530 &valid_p, complain);
7531 /* The static_cast or reinterpret_cast may be followed by a
7532 const_cast. */
7533 if (valid_p
7534 /* A valid cast may result in errors if, for example, a
7535 conversion to an ambiguous base class is required. */
7536 && !error_operand_p (result))
7537 {
7538 tree result_type;
7539
7540 maybe_warn_about_useless_cast (type, value, complain);
7541
7542 /* Non-class rvalues always have cv-unqualified type. */
7543 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
7544 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
7545 result_type = TREE_TYPE (result);
7546 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (result_type) && TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE)
7547 result_type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (result_type);
7548 /* If the type of RESULT does not match TYPE, perform a
7549 const_cast to make it match. If the static_cast or
7550 reinterpret_cast succeeded, we will differ by at most
7551 cv-qualification, so the follow-on const_cast is guaranteed
7552 to succeed. */
7553 if (!same_type_p (non_reference (type), non_reference (result_type)))
7554 {
7555 result = build_const_cast_1 (type, result, false, &valid_p);
7556 gcc_assert (valid_p);
7557 }
7558 return result;
7559 }
7560
7561 return error_mark_node;
7562}
7563
7564/* For use from the C common bits. */
7565tree
7566build_modify_expr (location_t location,
7567 tree lhs, tree /*lhs_origtype*/,
7568 enum tree_code modifycode,
7569 location_t /*rhs_location*/, tree rhs,
7570 tree /*rhs_origtype*/)
7571{
7572 return cp_build_modify_expr (location, lhs, modifycode, rhs,
7573 tf_warning_or_error);
7574}
7575
7576/* Build an assignment expression of lvalue LHS from value RHS.
7577 MODIFYCODE is the code for a binary operator that we use
7578 to combine the old value of LHS with RHS to get the new value.
7579 Or else MODIFYCODE is NOP_EXPR meaning do a simple assignment.
7580
7581 C++: If MODIFYCODE is INIT_EXPR, then leave references unbashed. */
7582
7583tree
7584cp_build_modify_expr (location_t loc, tree lhs, enum tree_code modifycode,
7585 tree rhs, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7586{
7587 tree result = NULL_TREE;
7588 tree newrhs = rhs;
7589 tree lhstype = TREE_TYPE (lhs);
7590 tree olhs = lhs;
7591 tree olhstype = lhstype;
7592 bool plain_assign = (modifycode == NOP_EXPR);
7593 bool compound_side_effects_p = false;
7594 tree preeval = NULL_TREE;
7595
7596 /* Avoid duplicate error messages from operands that had errors. */
7597 if (error_operand_p (lhs) || error_operand_p (rhs))
7598 return error_mark_node;
7599
7600 while (TREE_CODE (lhs) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
7601 {
7602 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 0)))
7603 compound_side_effects_p = true;
7604 lhs = TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1);
7605 }
7606
7607 /* Handle control structure constructs used as "lvalues". Note that we
7608 leave COMPOUND_EXPR on the LHS because it is sequenced after the RHS. */
7609 switch (TREE_CODE (lhs))
7610 {
7611 /* Handle --foo = 5; as these are valid constructs in C++. */
7612 case PREDECREMENT_EXPR:
7613 case PREINCREMENT_EXPR:
7614 if (compound_side_effects_p)
7615 newrhs = rhs = stabilize_expr (rhs, &preeval);
7616 lhs = genericize_compound_lvalue (lhs);
7617 maybe_add_compound:
7618 /* If we had (bar, --foo) = 5; or (bar, (baz, --foo)) = 5;
7619 and looked through the COMPOUND_EXPRs, readd them now around
7620 the resulting lhs. */
7621 if (TREE_CODE (olhs) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
7622 {
7623 lhs = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, lhstype, TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 0), lhs);
7624 tree *ptr = &TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1);
7625 for (olhs = TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 1);
7626 TREE_CODE (olhs) == COMPOUND_EXPR;
7627 olhs = TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 1))
7628 {
7629 *ptr = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, lhstype,
7630 TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 0), *ptr);
7631 ptr = &TREE_OPERAND (*ptr, 1);
7632 }
7633 }
7634 break;
7635
7636 case MODIFY_EXPR:
7637 if (compound_side_effects_p)
7638 newrhs = rhs = stabilize_expr (rhs, &preeval);
7639 lhs = genericize_compound_lvalue (lhs);
7640 goto maybe_add_compound;
7641
7642 case MIN_EXPR:
7643 case MAX_EXPR:
7644 /* MIN_EXPR and MAX_EXPR are currently only permitted as lvalues,
7645 when neither operand has side-effects. */
7646 if (!lvalue_or_else (lhs, lv_assign, complain))
7647 return error_mark_node;
7648
7649 gcc_assert (!TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 0))
7650 && !TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1)));
7651
7652 lhs = build3 (COND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (lhs),
7653 build2 (TREE_CODE (lhs) == MIN_EXPR ? LE_EXPR : GE_EXPR,
7654 boolean_type_node,
7655 TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 0),
7656 TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1)),
7657 TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 0),
7658 TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1));
7659 gcc_fallthrough ();
7660
7661 /* Handle (a ? b : c) used as an "lvalue". */
7662 case COND_EXPR:
7663 {
7664 /* Produce (a ? (b = rhs) : (c = rhs))
7665 except that the RHS goes through a save-expr
7666 so the code to compute it is only emitted once. */
7667 tree cond;
7668
7669 if (VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (rhs)))
7670 {
7671 if (complain & tf_error)
7672 error ("void value not ignored as it ought to be");
7673 return error_mark_node;
7674 }
7675
7676 rhs = stabilize_expr (rhs, &preeval);
7677
7678 /* Check this here to avoid odd errors when trying to convert
7679 a throw to the type of the COND_EXPR. */
7680 if (!lvalue_or_else (lhs, lv_assign, complain))
7681 return error_mark_node;
7682
7683 cond = build_conditional_expr
7684 (input_location, TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 0),
7685 cp_build_modify_expr (loc, TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1),
7686 modifycode, rhs, complain),
7687 cp_build_modify_expr (loc, TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 2),
7688 modifycode, rhs, complain),
7689 complain);
7690
7691 if (cond == error_mark_node)
7692 return cond;
7693 /* If we had (e, (a ? b : c)) = d; or (e, (f, (a ? b : c))) = d;
7694 and looked through the COMPOUND_EXPRs, readd them now around
7695 the resulting cond before adding the preevaluated rhs. */
7696 if (TREE_CODE (olhs) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
7697 {
7698 cond = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (cond),
7699 TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 0), cond);
7700 tree *ptr = &TREE_OPERAND (cond, 1);
7701 for (olhs = TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 1);
7702 TREE_CODE (olhs) == COMPOUND_EXPR;
7703 olhs = TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 1))
7704 {
7705 *ptr = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (cond),
7706 TREE_OPERAND (olhs, 0), *ptr);
7707 ptr = &TREE_OPERAND (*ptr, 1);
7708 }
7709 }
7710 /* Make sure the code to compute the rhs comes out
7711 before the split. */
7712 result = cond;
7713 goto ret;
7714 }
7715
7716 default:
7717 lhs = olhs;
7718 break;
7719 }
7720
7721 if (modifycode == INIT_EXPR)
7722 {
7723 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (rhs))
7724 /* Do the default thing. */;
7725 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == CONSTRUCTOR)
7726 {
7727 /* Compound literal. */
7728 if (! same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (rhs), lhstype))
7729 /* Call convert to generate an error; see PR 11063. */
7730 rhs = convert (lhstype, rhs);
7731 result = build2 (INIT_EXPR, lhstype, lhs, rhs);
7732 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (result) = 1;
7733 goto ret;
7734 }
7735 else if (! MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (lhstype))
7736 /* Do the default thing. */;
7737 else
7738 {
7739 vec<tree, va_gc> *rhs_vec = make_tree_vector_single (rhs);
7740 result = build_special_member_call (lhs, complete_ctor_identifier,
7741 &rhs_vec, lhstype, LOOKUP_NORMAL,
7742 complain);
7743 release_tree_vector (rhs_vec);
7744 if (result == NULL_TREE)
7745 return error_mark_node;
7746 goto ret;
7747 }
7748 }
7749 else
7750 {
7751 lhs = require_complete_type_sfinae (lhs, complain);
7752 if (lhs == error_mark_node)
7753 return error_mark_node;
7754
7755 if (modifycode == NOP_EXPR)
7756 {
7757 if (c_dialect_objc ())
7758 {
7759 result = objc_maybe_build_modify_expr (lhs, rhs);
7760 if (result)
7761 goto ret;
7762 }
7763
7764 /* `operator=' is not an inheritable operator. */
7765 if (! MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (lhstype))
7766 /* Do the default thing. */;
7767 else
7768 {
7769 result = build_new_op (input_location, MODIFY_EXPR,
7770 LOOKUP_NORMAL, lhs, rhs,
7771 make_node (NOP_EXPR), /*overload=*/NULL,
7772 complain);
7773 if (result == NULL_TREE)
7774 return error_mark_node;
7775 goto ret;
7776 }
7777 lhstype = olhstype;
7778 }
7779 else
7780 {
7781 tree init = NULL_TREE;
7782
7783 /* A binary op has been requested. Combine the old LHS
7784 value with the RHS producing the value we should actually
7785 store into the LHS. */
7786 gcc_assert (!((TREE_CODE (lhstype) == REFERENCE_TYPE
7787 && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (lhstype)))
7788 || MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (lhstype)));
7789
7790 /* Preevaluate the RHS to make sure its evaluation is complete
7791 before the lvalue-to-rvalue conversion of the LHS:
7792
7793 [expr.ass] With respect to an indeterminately-sequenced
7794 function call, the operation of a compound assignment is a
7795 single evaluation. [ Note: Therefore, a function call shall
7796 not intervene between the lvalue-to-rvalue conversion and the
7797 side effect associated with any single compound assignment
7798 operator. -- end note ] */
7799 lhs = cp_stabilize_reference (lhs);
7800 rhs = rvalue (rhs);
7801 rhs = stabilize_expr (rhs, &init);
7802 newrhs = cp_build_binary_op (loc, modifycode, lhs, rhs, complain);
7803 if (newrhs == error_mark_node)
7804 {
7805 if (complain & tf_error)
7806 error (" in evaluation of %<%Q(%#T, %#T)%>", modifycode,
7807 TREE_TYPE (lhs), TREE_TYPE (rhs));
7808 return error_mark_node;
7809 }
7810
7811 if (init)
7812 newrhs = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (newrhs), init, newrhs);
7813
7814 /* Now it looks like a plain assignment. */
7815 modifycode = NOP_EXPR;
7816 if (c_dialect_objc ())
7817 {
7818 result = objc_maybe_build_modify_expr (lhs, newrhs);
7819 if (result)
7820 goto ret;
7821 }
7822 }
7823 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (lhstype) != REFERENCE_TYPE);
7824 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (newrhs)) != REFERENCE_TYPE);
7825 }
7826
7827 /* The left-hand side must be an lvalue. */
7828 if (!lvalue_or_else (lhs, lv_assign, complain))
7829 return error_mark_node;
7830
7831 /* Warn about modifying something that is `const'. Don't warn if
7832 this is initialization. */
7833 if (modifycode != INIT_EXPR
7834 && (TREE_READONLY (lhs) || CP_TYPE_CONST_P (lhstype)
7835 /* Functions are not modifiable, even though they are
7836 lvalues. */
7837 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (lhs)) == FUNCTION_TYPE
7838 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (lhs)) == METHOD_TYPE
7839 /* If it's an aggregate and any field is const, then it is
7840 effectively const. */
7841 || (CLASS_TYPE_P (lhstype)
7842 && C_TYPE_FIELDS_READONLY (lhstype))))
7843 {
7844 if (complain & tf_error)
7845 cxx_readonly_error (lhs, lv_assign);
7846 else
7847 return error_mark_node;
7848 }
7849
7850 /* If storing into a structure or union member, it may have been given a
7851 lowered bitfield type. We need to convert to the declared type first,
7852 so retrieve it now. */
7853
7854 olhstype = unlowered_expr_type (lhs);
7855
7856 /* Convert new value to destination type. */
7857
7858 if (TREE_CODE (lhstype) == ARRAY_TYPE)
7859 {
7860 int from_array;
7861
7862 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (newrhs))
7863 {
7864 if (modifycode != INIT_EXPR)
7865 {
7866 if (complain & tf_error)
7867 error ("assigning to an array from an initializer list");
7868 return error_mark_node;
7869 }
7870 if (check_array_initializer (lhs, lhstype, newrhs))
7871 return error_mark_node;
7872 newrhs = digest_init (lhstype, newrhs, complain);
7873 if (newrhs == error_mark_node)
7874 return error_mark_node;
7875 }
7876
7877 /* C++11 8.5/17: "If the destination type is an array of characters,
7878 an array of char16_t, an array of char32_t, or an array of wchar_t,
7879 and the initializer is a string literal...". */
7880 else if (TREE_CODE (newrhs) == STRING_CST
7881 && char_type_p (TREE_TYPE (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (lhstype)))
7882 && modifycode == INIT_EXPR)
7883 {
7884 newrhs = digest_init (lhstype, newrhs, complain);
7885 if (newrhs == error_mark_node)
7886 return error_mark_node;
7887 }
7888
7889 else if (!same_or_base_type_p (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (lhstype),
7890 TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (newrhs))))
7891 {
7892 if (complain & tf_error)
7893 error ("incompatible types in assignment of %qT to %qT",
7894 TREE_TYPE (rhs), lhstype);
7895 return error_mark_node;
7896 }
7897
7898 /* Allow array assignment in compiler-generated code. */
7899 else if (!current_function_decl
7900 || !DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (current_function_decl))
7901 {
7902 /* This routine is used for both initialization and assignment.
7903 Make sure the diagnostic message differentiates the context. */
7904 if (complain & tf_error)
7905 {
7906 if (modifycode == INIT_EXPR)
7907 error ("array used as initializer");
7908 else
7909 error ("invalid array assignment");
7910 }
7911 return error_mark_node;
7912 }
7913
7914 from_array = TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (newrhs)) == ARRAY_TYPE
7915 ? 1 + (modifycode != INIT_EXPR): 0;
7916 result = build_vec_init (lhs, NULL_TREE, newrhs,
7917 /*explicit_value_init_p=*/false,
7918 from_array, complain);
7919 goto ret;
7920 }
7921
7922 if (modifycode == INIT_EXPR)
7923 /* Calls with INIT_EXPR are all direct-initialization, so don't set
7924 LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING. */
7925 newrhs = convert_for_initialization (lhs, olhstype, newrhs, LOOKUP_NORMAL,
7926 ICR_INIT, NULL_TREE, 0,
7927 complain);
7928 else
7929 newrhs = convert_for_assignment (olhstype, newrhs, ICR_ASSIGN,
7930 NULL_TREE, 0, complain, LOOKUP_IMPLICIT);
7931
7932 if (!same_type_p (lhstype, olhstype))
7933 newrhs = cp_convert_and_check (lhstype, newrhs, complain);
7934
7935 if (modifycode != INIT_EXPR)
7936 {
7937 if (TREE_CODE (newrhs) == CALL_EXPR
7938 && TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING (lhstype))
7939 newrhs = build_cplus_new (lhstype, newrhs, complain);
7940
7941 /* Can't initialize directly from a TARGET_EXPR, since that would
7942 cause the lhs to be constructed twice, and possibly result in
7943 accidental self-initialization. So we force the TARGET_EXPR to be
7944 expanded without a target. */
7945 if (TREE_CODE (newrhs) == TARGET_EXPR)
7946 newrhs = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (newrhs), newrhs,
7947 TREE_OPERAND (newrhs, 0));
7948 }
7949
7950 if (newrhs == error_mark_node)
7951 return error_mark_node;
7952
7953 if (c_dialect_objc () && flag_objc_gc)
7954 {
7955 result = objc_generate_write_barrier (lhs, modifycode, newrhs);
7956
7957 if (result)
7958 goto ret;
7959 }
7960
7961 result = build2 (modifycode == NOP_EXPR ? MODIFY_EXPR : INIT_EXPR,
7962 lhstype, lhs, newrhs);
7963
7964 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (result) = 1;
7965 if (!plain_assign)
7966 TREE_NO_WARNING (result) = 1;
7967
7968 ret:
7969 if (preeval)
7970 result = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (result), preeval, result);
7971 return result;
7972}
7973
7974cp_expr
7975build_x_modify_expr (location_t loc, tree lhs, enum tree_code modifycode,
7976 tree rhs, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7977{
7978 tree orig_lhs = lhs;
7979 tree orig_rhs = rhs;
7980 tree overload = NULL_TREE;
7981 tree op = build_nt (modifycode, NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
7982
7983 if (processing_template_decl)
7984 {
7985 if (modifycode == NOP_EXPR
7986 || type_dependent_expression_p (lhs)
7987 || type_dependent_expression_p (rhs))
7988 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, MODOP_EXPR, lhs,
7989 build_min_nt_loc (loc, modifycode, NULL_TREE,
7990 NULL_TREE), rhs);
7991
7992 lhs = build_non_dependent_expr (lhs);
7993 rhs = build_non_dependent_expr (rhs);
7994 }
7995
7996 if (modifycode != NOP_EXPR)
7997 {
7998 tree rval = build_new_op (loc, MODIFY_EXPR, LOOKUP_NORMAL,
7999 lhs, rhs, op, &overload, complain);
8000 if (rval)
8001 {
8002 if (rval == error_mark_node)
8003 return rval;
8004 TREE_NO_WARNING (rval) = 1;
8005 if (processing_template_decl)
8006 {
8007 if (overload != NULL_TREE)
8008 return (build_min_non_dep_op_overload
8009 (MODIFY_EXPR, rval, overload, orig_lhs, orig_rhs));
8010
8011 return (build_min_non_dep
8012 (MODOP_EXPR, rval, orig_lhs, op, orig_rhs));
8013 }
8014 return rval;
8015 }
8016 }
8017 return cp_build_modify_expr (loc, lhs, modifycode, rhs, complain);
8018}
8019
8020/* Helper function for get_delta_difference which assumes FROM is a base
8021 class of TO. Returns a delta for the conversion of pointer-to-member
8022 of FROM to pointer-to-member of TO. If the conversion is invalid and
8023 tf_error is not set in COMPLAIN returns error_mark_node, otherwise
8024 returns zero. If FROM is not a base class of TO, returns NULL_TREE.
8025 If C_CAST_P is true, this conversion is taking place as part of a
8026 C-style cast. */
8027
8028static tree
8029get_delta_difference_1 (tree from, tree to, bool c_cast_p,
8030 tsubst_flags_t complain)
8031{
8032 tree binfo;
8033 base_kind kind;
8034
8035 binfo = lookup_base (to, from, c_cast_p ? ba_unique : ba_check,
8036 &kind, complain);
8037
8038 if (binfo == error_mark_node)
8039 {
8040 if (!(complain & tf_error))
8041 return error_mark_node;
8042
8043 error (" in pointer to member function conversion");
8044 return size_zero_node;
8045 }
8046 else if (binfo)
8047 {
8048 if (kind != bk_via_virtual)
8049 return BINFO_OFFSET (binfo);
8050 else
8051 /* FROM is a virtual base class of TO. Issue an error or warning
8052 depending on whether or not this is a reinterpret cast. */
8053 {
8054 if (!(complain & tf_error))
8055 return error_mark_node;
8056
8057 error ("pointer to member conversion via virtual base %qT",
8058 BINFO_TYPE (binfo_from_vbase (binfo)));
8059
8060 return size_zero_node;
8061 }
8062 }
8063 else
8064 return NULL_TREE;
8065}
8066
8067/* Get difference in deltas for different pointer to member function
8068 types. If the conversion is invalid and tf_error is not set in
8069 COMPLAIN, returns error_mark_node, otherwise returns an integer
8070 constant of type PTRDIFF_TYPE_NODE and its value is zero if the
8071 conversion is invalid. If ALLOW_INVERSE_P is true, then allow reverse
8072 conversions as well. If C_CAST_P is true this conversion is taking
8073 place as part of a C-style cast.
8074
8075 Note that the naming of FROM and TO is kind of backwards; the return
8076 value is what we add to a TO in order to get a FROM. They are named
8077 this way because we call this function to find out how to convert from
8078 a pointer to member of FROM to a pointer to member of TO. */
8079
8080static tree
8081get_delta_difference (tree from, tree to,
8082 bool allow_inverse_p,
8083 bool c_cast_p, tsubst_flags_t complain)
8084{
8085 tree result;
8086
8087 if (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p (from, to))
8088 /* Pointer to member of incomplete class is permitted*/
8089 result = size_zero_node;
8090 else
8091 result = get_delta_difference_1 (from, to, c_cast_p, complain);
8092
8093 if (result == error_mark_node)
8094 return error_mark_node;
8095
8096 if (!result)
8097 {
8098 if (!allow_inverse_p)
8099 {
8100 if (!(complain & tf_error))
8101 return error_mark_node;
8102
8103 error_not_base_type (from, to);
8104 error (" in pointer to member conversion");
8105 result = size_zero_node;
8106 }
8107 else
8108 {
8109 result = get_delta_difference_1 (to, from, c_cast_p, complain);
8110
8111 if (result == error_mark_node)
8112 return error_mark_node;
8113
8114 if (result)
8115 result = size_diffop_loc (input_location,
8116 size_zero_node, result);
8117 else
8118 {
8119 if (!(complain & tf_error))
8120 return error_mark_node;
8121
8122 error_not_base_type (from, to);
8123 error (" in pointer to member conversion");
8124 result = size_zero_node;
8125 }
8126 }
8127 }
8128
8129 return convert_to_integer (ptrdiff_type_node, result);
8130}
8131
8132/* Return a constructor for the pointer-to-member-function TYPE using
8133 the other components as specified. */
8134
8135tree
8136build_ptrmemfunc1 (tree type, tree delta, tree pfn)
8137{
8138 tree u = NULL_TREE;
8139 tree delta_field;
8140 tree pfn_field;
8141 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v;
8142
8143 /* Pull the FIELD_DECLs out of the type. */
8144 pfn_field = TYPE_FIELDS (type);
8145 delta_field = DECL_CHAIN (pfn_field);
8146
8147 /* Make sure DELTA has the type we want. */
8148 delta = convert_and_check (input_location, delta_type_node, delta);
8149
8150 /* Convert to the correct target type if necessary. */
8151 pfn = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (pfn_field), pfn);
8152
8153 /* Finish creating the initializer. */
8154 vec_alloc (v, 2);
8155 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT(v, pfn_field, pfn);
8156 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT(v, delta_field, delta);
8157 u = build_constructor (type, v);
8158 TREE_CONSTANT (u) = TREE_CONSTANT (pfn) & TREE_CONSTANT (delta);
8159 TREE_STATIC (u) = (TREE_CONSTANT (u)
8160 && (initializer_constant_valid_p (pfn, TREE_TYPE (pfn))
8161 != NULL_TREE)
8162 && (initializer_constant_valid_p (delta, TREE_TYPE (delta))
8163 != NULL_TREE));
8164 return u;
8165}
8166
8167/* Build a constructor for a pointer to member function. It can be
8168 used to initialize global variables, local variable, or used
8169 as a value in expressions. TYPE is the POINTER to METHOD_TYPE we
8170 want to be.
8171
8172 If FORCE is nonzero, then force this conversion, even if
8173 we would rather not do it. Usually set when using an explicit
8174 cast. A C-style cast is being processed iff C_CAST_P is true.
8175
8176 Return error_mark_node, if something goes wrong. */
8177
8178tree
8179build_ptrmemfunc (tree type, tree pfn, int force, bool c_cast_p,
8180 tsubst_flags_t complain)
8181{
8182 tree fn;
8183 tree pfn_type;
8184 tree to_type;
8185
8186 if (error_operand_p (pfn))
8187 return error_mark_node;
8188
8189 pfn_type = TREE_TYPE (pfn);
8190 to_type = build_ptrmemfunc_type (type);
8191
8192 /* Handle multiple conversions of pointer to member functions. */
8193 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (pfn_type))
8194 {
8195 tree delta = NULL_TREE;
8196 tree npfn = NULL_TREE;
8197 tree n;
8198
8199 if (!force
8200 && !can_convert_arg (to_type, TREE_TYPE (pfn), pfn,
8201 LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain))
8202 {
8203 if (complain & tf_error)
8204 error ("invalid conversion to type %qT from type %qT",
8205 to_type, pfn_type);
8206 else
8207 return error_mark_node;
8208 }
8209
8210 n = get_delta_difference (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_OBJECT_TYPE (pfn_type),
8211 TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_OBJECT_TYPE (to_type),
8212 force,
8213 c_cast_p, complain);
8214 if (n == error_mark_node)
8215 return error_mark_node;
8216
8217 /* We don't have to do any conversion to convert a
8218 pointer-to-member to its own type. But, we don't want to
8219 just return a PTRMEM_CST if there's an explicit cast; that
8220 cast should make the expression an invalid template argument. */
8221 if (TREE_CODE (pfn) != PTRMEM_CST)
8222 {
8223 if (same_type_p (to_type, pfn_type))
8224 return pfn;
8225 else if (integer_zerop (n))
8226 return build_reinterpret_cast (to_type, pfn,
8227 complain);
8228 }
8229
8230 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (pfn))
8231 pfn = save_expr (pfn);
8232
8233 /* Obtain the function pointer and the current DELTA. */
8234 if (TREE_CODE (pfn) == PTRMEM_CST)
8235 expand_ptrmemfunc_cst (pfn, &delta, &npfn);
8236 else
8237 {
8238 npfn = build_ptrmemfunc_access_expr (pfn, pfn_identifier);
8239 delta = build_ptrmemfunc_access_expr (pfn, delta_identifier);
8240 }
8241
8242 /* Just adjust the DELTA field. */
8243 gcc_assert (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
8244 (TREE_TYPE (delta), ptrdiff_type_node));
8245 if (TARGET_PTRMEMFUNC_VBIT_LOCATION == ptrmemfunc_vbit_in_delta)
8246 n = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
8247 LSHIFT_EXPR, n, integer_one_node,
8248 complain);
8249 delta = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
8250 PLUS_EXPR, delta, n, complain);
8251 return build_ptrmemfunc1 (to_type, delta, npfn);
8252 }
8253
8254 /* Handle null pointer to member function conversions. */
8255 if (null_ptr_cst_p (pfn))
8256 {
8257 pfn = cp_build_c_cast (type, pfn, complain);
8258 return build_ptrmemfunc1 (to_type,
8259 integer_zero_node,
8260 pfn);
8261 }
8262
8263 if (type_unknown_p (pfn))
8264 return instantiate_type (type, pfn, complain);
8265
8266 fn = TREE_OPERAND (pfn, 0);
8267 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL
8268 /* In a template, we will have preserved the
8269 OFFSET_REF. */
8270 || (processing_template_decl && TREE_CODE (fn) == OFFSET_REF));
8271 return make_ptrmem_cst (to_type, fn);
8272}
8273
8274/* Return the DELTA, IDX, PFN, and DELTA2 values for the PTRMEM_CST
8275 given by CST.
8276
8277 ??? There is no consistency as to the types returned for the above
8278 values. Some code acts as if it were a sizetype and some as if it were
8279 integer_type_node. */
8280
8281void
8282expand_ptrmemfunc_cst (tree cst, tree *delta, tree *pfn)
8283{
8284 tree type = TREE_TYPE (cst);
8285 tree fn = PTRMEM_CST_MEMBER (cst);
8286 tree ptr_class, fn_class;
8287
8288 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL);
8289
8290 /* The class that the function belongs to. */
8291 fn_class = DECL_CONTEXT (fn);
8292
8293 /* The class that we're creating a pointer to member of. */
8294 ptr_class = TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_OBJECT_TYPE (type);
8295
8296 /* First, calculate the adjustment to the function's class. */
8297 *delta = get_delta_difference (fn_class, ptr_class, /*force=*/0,
8298 /*c_cast_p=*/0, tf_warning_or_error);
8299
8300 if (!DECL_VIRTUAL_P (fn))
8301 *pfn = convert (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (type),
8302 build_addr_func (fn, tf_warning_or_error));
8303 else
8304 {
8305 /* If we're dealing with a virtual function, we have to adjust 'this'
8306 again, to point to the base which provides the vtable entry for
8307 fn; the call will do the opposite adjustment. */
8308 tree orig_class = DECL_CONTEXT (fn);
8309 tree binfo = binfo_or_else (orig_class, fn_class);
8310 *delta = fold_build2 (PLUS_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (*delta),
8311 *delta, BINFO_OFFSET (binfo));
8312
8313 /* We set PFN to the vtable offset at which the function can be
8314 found, plus one (unless ptrmemfunc_vbit_in_delta, in which
8315 case delta is shifted left, and then incremented). */
8316 *pfn = DECL_VINDEX (fn);
8317 *pfn = fold_build2 (MULT_EXPR, integer_type_node, *pfn,
8318 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (vtable_entry_type));
8319
8320 switch (TARGET_PTRMEMFUNC_VBIT_LOCATION)
8321 {
8322 case ptrmemfunc_vbit_in_pfn:
8323 *pfn = fold_build2 (PLUS_EXPR, integer_type_node, *pfn,
8324 integer_one_node);
8325 break;
8326
8327 case ptrmemfunc_vbit_in_delta:
8328 *delta = fold_build2 (LSHIFT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (*delta),
8329 *delta, integer_one_node);
8330 *delta = fold_build2 (PLUS_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (*delta),
8331 *delta, integer_one_node);
8332 break;
8333
8334 default:
8335 gcc_unreachable ();
8336 }
8337
8338 *pfn = fold_convert (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (type), *pfn);
8339 }
8340}
8341
8342/* Return an expression for PFN from the pointer-to-member function
8343 given by T. */
8344
8345static tree
8346pfn_from_ptrmemfunc (tree t)
8347{
8348 if (TREE_CODE (t) == PTRMEM_CST)
8349 {
8350 tree delta;
8351 tree pfn;
8352
8353 expand_ptrmemfunc_cst (t, &delta, &pfn);
8354 if (pfn)
8355 return pfn;
8356 }
8357
8358 return build_ptrmemfunc_access_expr (t, pfn_identifier);
8359}
8360
8361/* Return an expression for DELTA from the pointer-to-member function
8362 given by T. */
8363
8364static tree
8365delta_from_ptrmemfunc (tree t)
8366{
8367 if (TREE_CODE (t) == PTRMEM_CST)
8368 {
8369 tree delta;
8370 tree pfn;
8371
8372 expand_ptrmemfunc_cst (t, &delta, &pfn);
8373 if (delta)
8374 return delta;
8375 }
8376
8377 return build_ptrmemfunc_access_expr (t, delta_identifier);
8378}
8379
8380/* Convert value RHS to type TYPE as preparation for an assignment to
8381 an lvalue of type TYPE. ERRTYPE indicates what kind of error the
8382 implicit conversion is. If FNDECL is non-NULL, we are doing the
8383 conversion in order to pass the PARMNUMth argument of FNDECL.
8384 If FNDECL is NULL, we are doing the conversion in function pointer
8385 argument passing, conversion in initialization, etc. */
8386
8387static tree
8388convert_for_assignment (tree type, tree rhs,
8389 impl_conv_rhs errtype, tree fndecl, int parmnum,
8390 tsubst_flags_t complain, int flags)
8391{
8392 tree rhstype;
8393 enum tree_code coder;
8394
8395 /* Strip NON_LVALUE_EXPRs since we aren't using as an lvalue. */
8396 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == NON_LVALUE_EXPR)
8397 rhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
8398
8399 /* Handle [dcl.init.list] direct-list-initialization from
8400 single element of enumeration with a fixed underlying type. */
8401 if (is_direct_enum_init (type, rhs))
8402 {
8403 tree elt = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (rhs, 0)->value;
8404 if (check_narrowing (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (type), elt, complain))
8405 {
8406 warning_sentinel w (warn_useless_cast);
8407 rhs = cp_build_c_cast (type, elt, complain);
8408 }
8409 else
8410 rhs = error_mark_node;
8411 }
8412
8413 rhstype = TREE_TYPE (rhs);
8414 coder = TREE_CODE (rhstype);
8415
8416 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type) && coder == VECTOR_TYPE
8417 && vector_types_convertible_p (type, rhstype, true))
8418 {
8419 rhs = mark_rvalue_use (rhs);
8420 return convert (type, rhs);
8421 }
8422
8423 if (rhs == error_mark_node || rhstype == error_mark_node)
8424 return error_mark_node;
8425 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == TREE_LIST && TREE_VALUE (rhs) == error_mark_node)
8426 return error_mark_node;
8427
8428 /* The RHS of an assignment cannot have void type. */
8429 if (coder == VOID_TYPE)
8430 {
8431 if (complain & tf_error)
8432 error ("void value not ignored as it ought to be");
8433 return error_mark_node;
8434 }
8435
8436 if (c_dialect_objc ())
8437 {
8438 int parmno;
8439 tree selector;
8440 tree rname = fndecl;
8441
8442 switch (errtype)
8443 {
8444 case ICR_ASSIGN:
8445 parmno = -1;
8446 break;
8447 case ICR_INIT:
8448 parmno = -2;
8449 break;
8450 default:
8451 selector = objc_message_selector ();
8452 parmno = parmnum;
8453 if (selector && parmno > 1)
8454 {
8455 rname = selector;
8456 parmno -= 1;
8457 }
8458 }
8459
8460 if (objc_compare_types (type, rhstype, parmno, rname))
8461 {
8462 rhs = mark_rvalue_use (rhs);
8463 return convert (type, rhs);
8464 }
8465 }
8466
8467 /* [expr.ass]
8468
8469 The expression is implicitly converted (clause _conv_) to the
8470 cv-unqualified type of the left operand.
8471
8472 We allow bad conversions here because by the time we get to this point
8473 we are committed to doing the conversion. If we end up doing a bad
8474 conversion, convert_like will complain. */
8475 if (!can_convert_arg_bad (type, rhstype, rhs, flags, complain))
8476 {
8477 /* When -Wno-pmf-conversions is use, we just silently allow
8478 conversions from pointers-to-members to plain pointers. If
8479 the conversion doesn't work, cp_convert will complain. */
8480 if (!warn_pmf2ptr
8481 && TYPE_PTR_P (type)
8482 && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (rhstype))
8483 rhs = cp_convert (strip_top_quals (type), rhs, complain);
8484 else
8485 {
8486 if (complain & tf_error)
8487 {
8488 /* If the right-hand side has unknown type, then it is an
8489 overloaded function. Call instantiate_type to get error
8490 messages. */
8491 if (rhstype == unknown_type_node)
8492 {
8493 tree r = instantiate_type (type, rhs, tf_warning_or_error);
8494 /* -fpermissive might allow this; recurse. */
8495 if (!seen_error ())
8496 return convert_for_assignment (type, r, errtype, fndecl,
8497 parmnum, complain, flags);
8498 }
8499 else if (fndecl)
8500 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT for argument %qP to %qD",
8501 rhstype, type, parmnum, fndecl);
8502 else
8503 switch (errtype)
8504 {
8505 case ICR_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT:
8506 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT in default argument",
8507 rhstype, type);
8508 break;
8509 case ICR_ARGPASS:
8510 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT in argument passing",
8511 rhstype, type);
8512 break;
8513 case ICR_CONVERTING:
8514 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT",
8515 rhstype, type);
8516 break;
8517 case ICR_INIT:
8518 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT in initialization",
8519 rhstype, type);
8520 break;
8521 case ICR_RETURN:
8522 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT in return",
8523 rhstype, type);
8524 break;
8525 case ICR_ASSIGN:
8526 error ("cannot convert %qT to %qT in assignment",
8527 rhstype, type);
8528 break;
8529 default:
8530 gcc_unreachable();
8531 }
8532 if (TYPE_PTR_P (rhstype)
8533 && TYPE_PTR_P (type)
8534 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (rhstype))
8535 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type))
8536 && !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (rhstype)))
8537 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL
8538 (TREE_TYPE (rhstype))),
8539 "class type %qT is incomplete", TREE_TYPE (rhstype));
8540 }
8541 return error_mark_node;
8542 }
8543 }
8544 if (warn_suggest_attribute_format)
8545 {
8546 const enum tree_code codel = TREE_CODE (type);
8547 if ((codel == POINTER_TYPE || codel == REFERENCE_TYPE)
8548 && coder == codel
8549 && check_missing_format_attribute (type, rhstype)
8550 && (complain & tf_warning))
8551 switch (errtype)
8552 {
8553 case ICR_ARGPASS:
8554 case ICR_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT:
8555 if (fndecl)
8556 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
8557 "parameter %qP of %qD might be a candidate "
8558 "for a format attribute", parmnum, fndecl);
8559 else
8560 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
8561 "parameter might be a candidate "
8562 "for a format attribute");
8563 break;
8564 case ICR_CONVERTING:
8565 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
8566 "target of conversion might be a candidate "
8567 "for a format attribute");
8568 break;
8569 case ICR_INIT:
8570 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
8571 "target of initialization might be a candidate "
8572 "for a format attribute");
8573 break;
8574 case ICR_RETURN:
8575 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
8576 "return type might be a candidate "
8577 "for a format attribute");
8578 break;
8579 case ICR_ASSIGN:
8580 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
8581 "left-hand side of assignment might be a candidate "
8582 "for a format attribute");
8583 break;
8584 default:
8585 gcc_unreachable();
8586 }
8587 }
8588
8589 /* If -Wparentheses, warn about a = b = c when a has type bool and b
8590 does not. */
8591 if (warn_parentheses
8592 && TREE_CODE (type) == BOOLEAN_TYPE
8593 && TREE_CODE (rhs) == MODIFY_EXPR
8594 && !TREE_NO_WARNING (rhs)
8595 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (rhs)) != BOOLEAN_TYPE
8596 && (complain & tf_warning))
8597 {
8598 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (rhs, input_location);
8599
8600 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wparentheses,
8601 "suggest parentheses around assignment used as truth value");
8602 TREE_NO_WARNING (rhs) = 1;
8603 }
8604
8605 return perform_implicit_conversion_flags (strip_top_quals (type), rhs,
8606 complain, flags);
8607}
8608
8609/* Convert RHS to be of type TYPE.
8610 If EXP is nonzero, it is the target of the initialization.
8611 ERRTYPE indicates what kind of error the implicit conversion is.
8612
8613 Two major differences between the behavior of
8614 `convert_for_assignment' and `convert_for_initialization'
8615 are that references are bashed in the former, while
8616 copied in the latter, and aggregates are assigned in
8617 the former (operator=) while initialized in the
8618 latter (X(X&)).
8619
8620 If using constructor make sure no conversion operator exists, if one does
8621 exist, an ambiguity exists. */
8622
8623tree
8624convert_for_initialization (tree exp, tree type, tree rhs, int flags,
8625 impl_conv_rhs errtype, tree fndecl, int parmnum,
8626 tsubst_flags_t complain)
8627{
8628 enum tree_code codel = TREE_CODE (type);
8629 tree rhstype;
8630 enum tree_code coder;
8631
8632 /* build_c_cast puts on a NOP_EXPR to make the result not an lvalue.
8633 Strip such NOP_EXPRs, since RHS is used in non-lvalue context. */
8634 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == NOP_EXPR
8635 && TREE_TYPE (rhs) == TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0))
8636 && codel != REFERENCE_TYPE)
8637 rhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
8638
8639 if (type == error_mark_node
8640 || rhs == error_mark_node
8641 || (TREE_CODE (rhs) == TREE_LIST && TREE_VALUE (rhs) == error_mark_node))
8642 return error_mark_node;
8643
8644 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (non_reference (type)))
8645 ;
8646 else if ((TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (rhs)) == ARRAY_TYPE
8647 && TREE_CODE (type) != ARRAY_TYPE
8648 && (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE
8649 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (type)) != ARRAY_TYPE))
8650 || (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (rhs)) == FUNCTION_TYPE
8651 && !TYPE_REFFN_P (type))
8652 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (rhs)) == METHOD_TYPE)
8653 rhs = decay_conversion (rhs, complain);
8654
8655 rhstype = TREE_TYPE (rhs);
8656 coder = TREE_CODE (rhstype);
8657
8658 if (coder == ERROR_MARK)
8659 return error_mark_node;
8660
8661 /* We accept references to incomplete types, so we can
8662 return here before checking if RHS is of complete type. */
8663
8664 if (codel == REFERENCE_TYPE)
8665 {
8666 /* This should eventually happen in convert_arguments. */
8667 int savew = 0, savee = 0;
8668
8669 if (fndecl)
8670 savew = warningcount + werrorcount, savee = errorcount;
8671 rhs = initialize_reference (type, rhs, flags, complain);
8672
8673 if (fndecl
8674 && (warningcount + werrorcount > savew || errorcount > savee))
8675 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fndecl),
8676 "in passing argument %P of %qD", parmnum, fndecl);
8677
8678 return rhs;
8679 }
8680
8681 if (exp != 0)
8682 exp = require_complete_type_sfinae (exp, complain);
8683 if (exp == error_mark_node)
8684 return error_mark_node;
8685
8686 rhstype = non_reference (rhstype);
8687
8688 type = complete_type (type);
8689
8690 if (DIRECT_INIT_EXPR_P (type, rhs))
8691 /* Don't try to do copy-initialization if we already have
8692 direct-initialization. */
8693 return rhs;
8694
8695 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
8696 return perform_implicit_conversion_flags (type, rhs, complain, flags);
8697
8698 return convert_for_assignment (type, rhs, errtype, fndecl, parmnum,
8699 complain, flags);
8700}
8701
8702/* If RETVAL is the address of, or a reference to, a local variable or
8703 temporary give an appropriate warning and return true. */
8704
8705static bool
8706maybe_warn_about_returning_address_of_local (tree retval)
8707{
8708 tree valtype = TREE_TYPE (DECL_RESULT (current_function_decl));
8709 tree whats_returned = fold_for_warn (retval);
8710
8711 for (;;)
8712 {
8713 if (TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
8714 whats_returned = TREE_OPERAND (whats_returned, 1);
8715 else if (CONVERT_EXPR_P (whats_returned)
8716 || TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == NON_LVALUE_EXPR)
8717 whats_returned = TREE_OPERAND (whats_returned, 0);
8718 else
8719 break;
8720 }
8721
8722 if (TREE_CODE (whats_returned) != ADDR_EXPR)
8723 return false;
8724 whats_returned = TREE_OPERAND (whats_returned, 0);
8725
8726 while (TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == COMPONENT_REF
8727 || TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == ARRAY_REF)
8728 whats_returned = TREE_OPERAND (whats_returned, 0);
8729
8730 if (TREE_CODE (valtype) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
8731 {
8732 if (TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == AGGR_INIT_EXPR
8733 || TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == TARGET_EXPR)
8734 {
8735 warning (OPT_Wreturn_local_addr, "returning reference to temporary");
8736 return true;
8737 }
8738 if (VAR_P (whats_returned)
8739 && DECL_NAME (whats_returned)
8740 && TEMP_NAME_P (DECL_NAME (whats_returned)))
8741 {
8742 warning (OPT_Wreturn_local_addr, "reference to non-lvalue returned");
8743 return true;
8744 }
8745 }
8746
8747 if (DECL_P (whats_returned)
8748 && DECL_NAME (whats_returned)
8749 && DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (whats_returned)
8750 && !is_capture_proxy (whats_returned)
8751 && !(TREE_STATIC (whats_returned)
8752 || TREE_PUBLIC (whats_returned)))
8753 {
8754 if (TREE_CODE (valtype) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
8755 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (whats_returned),
8756 OPT_Wreturn_local_addr,
8757 "reference to local variable %qD returned",
8758 whats_returned);
8759 else if (TREE_CODE (whats_returned) == LABEL_DECL)
8760 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (whats_returned),
8761 OPT_Wreturn_local_addr, "address of label %qD returned",
8762 whats_returned);
8763 else
8764 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (whats_returned),
8765 OPT_Wreturn_local_addr, "address of local variable %qD "
8766 "returned", whats_returned);
8767 return true;
8768 }
8769
8770 return false;
8771}
8772
8773/* Check that returning RETVAL from the current function is valid.
8774 Return an expression explicitly showing all conversions required to
8775 change RETVAL into the function return type, and to assign it to
8776 the DECL_RESULT for the function. Set *NO_WARNING to true if
8777 code reaches end of non-void function warning shouldn't be issued
8778 on this RETURN_EXPR. */
8779
8780tree
8781check_return_expr (tree retval, bool *no_warning)
8782{
8783 tree result;
8784 /* The type actually returned by the function. */
8785 tree valtype;
8786 /* The type the function is declared to return, or void if
8787 the declared type is incomplete. */
8788 tree functype;
8789 int fn_returns_value_p;
8790 bool named_return_value_okay_p;
8791
8792 *no_warning = false;
8793
8794 if (flag_cilkplus && retval && contains_cilk_spawn_stmt (retval))
8795 {
8796 error_at (EXPR_LOCATION (retval), "use of %<_Cilk_spawn%> in a return "
8797 "statement is not allowed");
8798 return NULL_TREE;
8799 }
8800
8801 /* A `volatile' function is one that isn't supposed to return, ever.
8802 (This is a G++ extension, used to get better code for functions
8803 that call the `volatile' function.) */
8804 if (TREE_THIS_VOLATILE (current_function_decl))
8805 warning (0, "function declared %<noreturn%> has a %<return%> statement");
8806
8807 /* Check for various simple errors. */
8808 if (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
8809 {
8810 if (retval)
8811 error ("returning a value from a destructor");
8812 return NULL_TREE;
8813 }
8814 else if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
8815 {
8816 if (in_function_try_handler)
8817 /* If a return statement appears in a handler of the
8818 function-try-block of a constructor, the program is ill-formed. */
8819 error ("cannot return from a handler of a function-try-block of a constructor");
8820 else if (retval)
8821 /* You can't return a value from a constructor. */
8822 error ("returning a value from a constructor");
8823 return NULL_TREE;
8824 }
8825
8826 const tree saved_retval = retval;
8827
8828 if (processing_template_decl)
8829 {
8830 current_function_returns_value = 1;
8831
8832 if (check_for_bare_parameter_packs (retval))
8833 return error_mark_node;
8834
8835 if (WILDCARD_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (DECL_RESULT (current_function_decl)))
8836 || (retval != NULL_TREE
8837 && type_dependent_expression_p (retval)))
8838 return retval;
8839 }
8840
8841 functype = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (current_function_decl));
8842
8843 /* Deduce auto return type from a return statement. */
8844 if (current_function_auto_return_pattern)
8845 {
8846 tree auto_node;
8847 tree type;
8848
8849 if (!retval && !is_auto (current_function_auto_return_pattern))
8850 {
8851 /* Give a helpful error message. */
8852 error ("return-statement with no value, in function returning %qT",
8853 current_function_auto_return_pattern);
8854 inform (input_location, "only plain %<auto%> return type can be "
8855 "deduced to %<void%>");
8856 type = error_mark_node;
8857 }
8858 else if (retval && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (retval))
8859 {
8860 error ("returning initializer list");
8861 type = error_mark_node;
8862 }
8863 else
8864 {
8865 if (!retval)
8866 retval = void_node;
8867 auto_node = type_uses_auto (current_function_auto_return_pattern);
8868 type = do_auto_deduction (current_function_auto_return_pattern,
8869 retval, auto_node);
8870 }
8871
8872 if (type == error_mark_node)
8873 /* Leave it. */;
8874 else if (functype == current_function_auto_return_pattern)
8875 apply_deduced_return_type (current_function_decl, type);
8876 else if (!same_type_p (type, functype))
8877 {
8878 if (LAMBDA_FUNCTION_P (current_function_decl))
8879 error ("inconsistent types %qT and %qT deduced for "
8880 "lambda return type", functype, type);
8881 else
8882 error ("inconsistent deduction for auto return type: "
8883 "%qT and then %qT", functype, type);
8884 }
8885 functype = type;
8886 }
8887
8888 result = DECL_RESULT (current_function_decl);
8889 valtype = TREE_TYPE (result);
8890 gcc_assert (valtype != NULL_TREE);
8891 fn_returns_value_p = !VOID_TYPE_P (valtype);
8892
8893 /* Check for a return statement with no return value in a function
8894 that's supposed to return a value. */
8895 if (!retval && fn_returns_value_p)
8896 {
8897 if (functype != error_mark_node)
8898 permerror (input_location, "return-statement with no value, in "
8899 "function returning %qT", valtype);
8900 /* Remember that this function did return. */
8901 current_function_returns_value = 1;
8902 /* And signal caller that TREE_NO_WARNING should be set on the
8903 RETURN_EXPR to avoid control reaches end of non-void function
8904 warnings in tree-cfg.c. */
8905 *no_warning = true;
8906 }
8907 /* Check for a return statement with a value in a function that
8908 isn't supposed to return a value. */
8909 else if (retval && !fn_returns_value_p)
8910 {
8911 if (VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (retval)))
8912 /* You can return a `void' value from a function of `void'
8913 type. In that case, we have to evaluate the expression for
8914 its side-effects. */
8915 finish_expr_stmt (retval);
8916 else
8917 permerror (input_location, "return-statement with a value, in function "
8918 "returning 'void'");
8919 current_function_returns_null = 1;
8920
8921 /* There's really no value to return, after all. */
8922 return NULL_TREE;
8923 }
8924 else if (!retval)
8925 /* Remember that this function can sometimes return without a
8926 value. */
8927 current_function_returns_null = 1;
8928 else
8929 /* Remember that this function did return a value. */
8930 current_function_returns_value = 1;
8931
8932 /* Check for erroneous operands -- but after giving ourselves a
8933 chance to provide an error about returning a value from a void
8934 function. */
8935 if (error_operand_p (retval))
8936 {
8937 current_function_return_value = error_mark_node;
8938 return error_mark_node;
8939 }
8940
8941 /* Only operator new(...) throw(), can return NULL [expr.new/13]. */
8942 if ((DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (current_function_decl) == NEW_EXPR
8943 || DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (current_function_decl) == VEC_NEW_EXPR)
8944 && !TYPE_NOTHROW_P (TREE_TYPE (current_function_decl))
8945 && ! flag_check_new
8946 && retval && null_ptr_cst_p (retval))
8947 warning (0, "%<operator new%> must not return NULL unless it is "
8948 "declared %<throw()%> (or -fcheck-new is in effect)");
8949
8950 /* Effective C++ rule 15. See also start_function. */
8951 if (warn_ecpp
8952 && DECL_NAME (current_function_decl) == cp_assignment_operator_id (NOP_EXPR))
8953 {
8954 bool warn = true;
8955
8956 /* The function return type must be a reference to the current
8957 class. */
8958 if (TREE_CODE (valtype) == REFERENCE_TYPE
8959 && same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
8960 (TREE_TYPE (valtype), TREE_TYPE (current_class_ref)))
8961 {
8962 /* Returning '*this' is obviously OK. */
8963 if (retval == current_class_ref)
8964 warn = false;
8965 /* If we are calling a function whose return type is the same of
8966 the current class reference, it is ok. */
8967 else if (INDIRECT_REF_P (retval)
8968 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (retval, 0)) == CALL_EXPR)
8969 warn = false;
8970 }
8971
8972 if (warn)
8973 warning (OPT_Weffc__, "%<operator=%> should return a reference to %<*this%>");
8974 }
8975
8976 if (processing_template_decl)
8977 {
8978 /* We should not have changed the return value. */
8979 gcc_assert (retval == saved_retval);
8980 return retval;
8981 }
8982
8983 /* The fabled Named Return Value optimization, as per [class.copy]/15:
8984
8985 [...] For a function with a class return type, if the expression
8986 in the return statement is the name of a local object, and the cv-
8987 unqualified type of the local object is the same as the function
8988 return type, an implementation is permitted to omit creating the tem-
8989 porary object to hold the function return value [...]
8990
8991 So, if this is a value-returning function that always returns the same
8992 local variable, remember it.
8993
8994 It might be nice to be more flexible, and choose the first suitable
8995 variable even if the function sometimes returns something else, but
8996 then we run the risk of clobbering the variable we chose if the other
8997 returned expression uses the chosen variable somehow. And people expect
8998 this restriction, anyway. (jason 2000-11-19)
8999
9000 See finish_function and finalize_nrv for the rest of this optimization. */
9001
9002 named_return_value_okay_p =
9003 (retval != NULL_TREE
9004 /* Must be a local, automatic variable. */
9005 && VAR_P (retval)
9006 && DECL_CONTEXT (retval) == current_function_decl
9007 && ! TREE_STATIC (retval)
9008 /* And not a lambda or anonymous union proxy. */
9009 && !DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (retval)
9010 && (DECL_ALIGN (retval) <= DECL_ALIGN (result))
9011 /* The cv-unqualified type of the returned value must be the
9012 same as the cv-unqualified return type of the
9013 function. */
9014 && same_type_p ((TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (retval))),
9015 (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (functype)))
9016 /* And the returned value must be non-volatile. */
9017 && ! TYPE_VOLATILE (TREE_TYPE (retval)));
9018
9019 if (fn_returns_value_p && flag_elide_constructors)
9020 {
9021 if (named_return_value_okay_p
9022 && (current_function_return_value == NULL_TREE
9023 || current_function_return_value == retval))
9024 current_function_return_value = retval;
9025 else
9026 current_function_return_value = error_mark_node;
9027 }
9028
9029 /* We don't need to do any conversions when there's nothing being
9030 returned. */
9031 if (!retval)
9032 return NULL_TREE;
9033
9034 /* Do any required conversions. */
9035 if (retval == result || DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (current_function_decl))
9036 /* No conversions are required. */
9037 ;
9038 else
9039 {
9040 int flags = LOOKUP_NORMAL | LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING;
9041
9042 /* The functype's return type will have been set to void, if it
9043 was an incomplete type. Just treat this as 'return;' */
9044 if (VOID_TYPE_P (functype))
9045 return error_mark_node;
9046
9047 /* If we had an id-expression obfuscated by force_paren_expr, we need
9048 to undo it so we can try to treat it as an rvalue below. */
9049 retval = maybe_undo_parenthesized_ref (retval);
9050
9051 /* Under C++11 [12.8/32 class.copy], a returned lvalue is sometimes
9052 treated as an rvalue for the purposes of overload resolution to
9053 favor move constructors over copy constructors.
9054
9055 Note that these conditions are similar to, but not as strict as,
9056 the conditions for the named return value optimization. */
9057 if ((cxx_dialect != cxx98)
9058 && ((VAR_P (retval) && !DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (retval))
9059 || TREE_CODE (retval) == PARM_DECL)
9060 && DECL_CONTEXT (retval) == current_function_decl
9061 && !TREE_STATIC (retval)
9062 /* This is only interesting for class type. */
9063 && CLASS_TYPE_P (functype))
9064 flags = flags | LOOKUP_PREFER_RVALUE;
9065
9066 /* First convert the value to the function's return type, then
9067 to the type of return value's location to handle the
9068 case that functype is smaller than the valtype. */
9069 retval = convert_for_initialization
9070 (NULL_TREE, functype, retval, flags, ICR_RETURN, NULL_TREE, 0,
9071 tf_warning_or_error);
9072 retval = convert (valtype, retval);
9073
9074 /* If the conversion failed, treat this just like `return;'. */
9075 if (retval == error_mark_node)
9076 return retval;
9077 /* We can't initialize a register from a AGGR_INIT_EXPR. */
9078 else if (! cfun->returns_struct
9079 && TREE_CODE (retval) == TARGET_EXPR
9080 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (retval, 1)) == AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
9081 retval = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (retval), retval,
9082 TREE_OPERAND (retval, 0));
9083 else if (maybe_warn_about_returning_address_of_local (retval))
9084 retval = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (retval), retval,
9085 build_zero_cst (TREE_TYPE (retval)));
9086 }
9087
9088 /* Actually copy the value returned into the appropriate location. */
9089 if (retval && retval != result)
9090 retval = build2 (INIT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (result), result, retval);
9091
9092 return retval;
9093}
9094
9095
9096/* Returns nonzero if the pointer-type FROM can be converted to the
9097 pointer-type TO via a qualification conversion. If CONSTP is -1,
9098 then we return nonzero if the pointers are similar, and the
9099 cv-qualification signature of FROM is a proper subset of that of TO.
9100
9101 If CONSTP is positive, then all outer pointers have been
9102 const-qualified. */
9103
9104static int
9105comp_ptr_ttypes_real (tree to, tree from, int constp)
9106{
9107 bool to_more_cv_qualified = false;
9108 bool is_opaque_pointer = false;
9109
9110 for (; ; to = TREE_TYPE (to), from = TREE_TYPE (from))
9111 {
9112 if (TREE_CODE (to) != TREE_CODE (from))
9113 return 0;
9114
9115 if (TREE_CODE (from) == OFFSET_TYPE
9116 && !same_type_p (TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (from),
9117 TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (to)))
9118 return 0;
9119
9120 /* Const and volatile mean something different for function types,
9121 so the usual checks are not appropriate. */
9122 if (TREE_CODE (to) != FUNCTION_TYPE && TREE_CODE (to) != METHOD_TYPE)
9123 {
9124 if (!at_least_as_qualified_p (to, from))
9125 return 0;
9126
9127 if (!at_least_as_qualified_p (from, to))
9128 {
9129 if (constp == 0)
9130 return 0;
9131 to_more_cv_qualified = true;
9132 }
9133
9134 if (constp > 0)
9135 constp &= TYPE_READONLY (to);
9136 }
9137
9138 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (to))
9139 is_opaque_pointer = vector_targets_convertible_p (to, from);
9140
9141 if (!TYPE_PTR_P (to) && !TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (to))
9142 return ((constp >= 0 || to_more_cv_qualified)
9143 && (is_opaque_pointer
9144 || same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p (to, from)));
9145 }
9146}
9147
9148/* When comparing, say, char ** to char const **, this function takes
9149 the 'char *' and 'char const *'. Do not pass non-pointer/reference
9150 types to this function. */
9151
9152int
9153comp_ptr_ttypes (tree to, tree from)
9154{
9155 return comp_ptr_ttypes_real (to, from, 1);
9156}
9157
9158/* Returns true iff FNTYPE is a non-class type that involves
9159 error_mark_node. We can get FUNCTION_TYPE with buried error_mark_node
9160 if a parameter type is ill-formed. */
9161
9162bool
9163error_type_p (const_tree type)
9164{
9165 tree t;
9166
9167 switch (TREE_CODE (type))
9168 {
9169 case ERROR_MARK:
9170 return true;
9171
9172 case POINTER_TYPE:
9173 case REFERENCE_TYPE:
9174 case OFFSET_TYPE:
9175 return error_type_p (TREE_TYPE (type));
9176
9177 case FUNCTION_TYPE:
9178 case METHOD_TYPE:
9179 if (error_type_p (TREE_TYPE (type)))
9180 return true;
9181 for (t = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type); t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
9182 if (error_type_p (TREE_VALUE (t)))
9183 return true;
9184 return false;
9185
9186 case RECORD_TYPE:
9187 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type))
9188 return error_type_p (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (type));
9189 return false;
9190
9191 default:
9192 return false;
9193 }
9194}
9195
9196/* Returns true if to and from are (possibly multi-level) pointers to the same
9197 type or inheritance-related types, regardless of cv-quals. */
9198
9199bool
9200ptr_reasonably_similar (const_tree to, const_tree from)
9201{
9202 for (; ; to = TREE_TYPE (to), from = TREE_TYPE (from))
9203 {
9204 /* Any target type is similar enough to void. */
9205 if (VOID_TYPE_P (to))
9206 return !error_type_p (from);
9207 if (VOID_TYPE_P (from))
9208 return !error_type_p (to);
9209
9210 if (TREE_CODE (to) != TREE_CODE (from))
9211 return false;
9212
9213 if (TREE_CODE (from) == OFFSET_TYPE
9214 && comptypes (TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (to),
9215 TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (from),
9216 COMPARE_BASE | COMPARE_DERIVED))
9217 continue;
9218
9219 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (to)
9220 && vector_types_convertible_p (to, from, false))
9221 return true;
9222
9223 if (TREE_CODE (to) == INTEGER_TYPE
9224 && TYPE_PRECISION (to) == TYPE_PRECISION (from))
9225 return true;
9226
9227 if (TREE_CODE (to) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
9228 return !error_type_p (to) && !error_type_p (from);
9229
9230 if (!TYPE_PTR_P (to))
9231 {
9232 /* When either type is incomplete avoid DERIVED_FROM_P,
9233 which may call complete_type (c++/57942). */
9234 bool b = !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (to) || !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (from);
9235 return comptypes
9236 (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (to), TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (from),
9237 b ? COMPARE_STRICT : COMPARE_BASE | COMPARE_DERIVED);
9238 }
9239 }
9240}
9241
9242/* Return true if TO and FROM (both of which are POINTER_TYPEs or
9243 pointer-to-member types) are the same, ignoring cv-qualification at
9244 all levels. */
9245
9246bool
9247comp_ptr_ttypes_const (tree to, tree from)
9248{
9249 bool is_opaque_pointer = false;
9250
9251 for (; ; to = TREE_TYPE (to), from = TREE_TYPE (from))
9252 {
9253 if (TREE_CODE (to) != TREE_CODE (from))
9254 return false;
9255
9256 if (TREE_CODE (from) == OFFSET_TYPE
9257 && same_type_p (TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (from),
9258 TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (to)))
9259 continue;
9260
9261 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (to))
9262 is_opaque_pointer = vector_targets_convertible_p (to, from);
9263
9264 if (!TYPE_PTR_P (to))
9265 return (is_opaque_pointer
9266 || same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p (to, from));
9267 }
9268}
9269
9270/* Returns the type qualifiers for this type, including the qualifiers on the
9271 elements for an array type. */
9272
9273int
9274cp_type_quals (const_tree type)
9275{
9276 int quals;
9277 /* This CONST_CAST is okay because strip_array_types returns its
9278 argument unmodified and we assign it to a const_tree. */
9279 type = strip_array_types (CONST_CAST_TREE (type));
9280 if (type == error_mark_node
9281 /* Quals on a FUNCTION_TYPE are memfn quals. */
9282 || TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
9283 return TYPE_UNQUALIFIED;
9284 quals = TYPE_QUALS (type);
9285 /* METHOD and REFERENCE_TYPEs should never have quals. */
9286 gcc_assert ((TREE_CODE (type) != METHOD_TYPE
9287 && TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE)
9288 || ((quals & (TYPE_QUAL_CONST|TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE))
9289 == TYPE_UNQUALIFIED));
9290 return quals;
9291}
9292
9293/* Returns the function-ref-qualifier for TYPE */
9294
9295cp_ref_qualifier
9296type_memfn_rqual (const_tree type)
9297{
9298 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
9299 || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE);
9300
9301 if (!FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED (type))
9302 return REF_QUAL_NONE;
9303 else if (FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED (type))
9304 return REF_QUAL_RVALUE;
9305 else
9306 return REF_QUAL_LVALUE;
9307}
9308
9309/* Returns the function-cv-quals for TYPE, which must be a FUNCTION_TYPE or
9310 METHOD_TYPE. */
9311
9312int
9313type_memfn_quals (const_tree type)
9314{
9315 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
9316 return TYPE_QUALS (type);
9317 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
9318 return cp_type_quals (class_of_this_parm (type));
9319 else
9320 gcc_unreachable ();
9321}
9322
9323/* Returns the FUNCTION_TYPE TYPE with its function-cv-quals changed to
9324 MEMFN_QUALS and its ref-qualifier to RQUAL. */
9325
9326tree
9327apply_memfn_quals (tree type, cp_cv_quals memfn_quals, cp_ref_qualifier rqual)
9328{
9329 /* Could handle METHOD_TYPE here if necessary. */
9330 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE);
9331 if (TYPE_QUALS (type) == memfn_quals
9332 && type_memfn_rqual (type) == rqual)
9333 return type;
9334
9335 /* This should really have a different TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT, but that gets
9336 complex. */
9337 tree result = build_qualified_type (type, memfn_quals);
9338 return build_ref_qualified_type (result, rqual);
9339}
9340
9341/* Returns nonzero if TYPE is const or volatile. */
9342
9343bool
9344cv_qualified_p (const_tree type)
9345{
9346 int quals = cp_type_quals (type);
9347 return (quals & (TYPE_QUAL_CONST|TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE)) != 0;
9348}
9349
9350/* Returns nonzero if the TYPE contains a mutable member. */
9351
9352bool
9353cp_has_mutable_p (const_tree type)
9354{
9355 /* This CONST_CAST is okay because strip_array_types returns its
9356 argument unmodified and we assign it to a const_tree. */
9357 type = strip_array_types (CONST_CAST_TREE(type));
9358
9359 return CLASS_TYPE_P (type) && CLASSTYPE_HAS_MUTABLE (type);
9360}
9361
9362/* Set TREE_READONLY and TREE_VOLATILE on DECL as indicated by the
9363 TYPE_QUALS. For a VAR_DECL, this may be an optimistic
9364 approximation. In particular, consider:
9365
9366 int f();
9367 struct S { int i; };
9368 const S s = { f(); }
9369
9370 Here, we will make "s" as TREE_READONLY (because it is declared
9371 "const") -- only to reverse ourselves upon seeing that the
9372 initializer is non-constant. */
9373
9374void
9375cp_apply_type_quals_to_decl (int type_quals, tree decl)
9376{
9377 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
9378
9379 if (type == error_mark_node)
9380 return;
9381
9382 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
9383 return;
9384
9385 gcc_assert (!(TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
9386 && type_quals != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED));
9387
9388 /* Avoid setting TREE_READONLY incorrectly. */
9389 /* We used to check TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING here, but now a constexpr
9390 constructor can produce constant init, so rely on cp_finish_decl to
9391 clear TREE_READONLY if the variable has non-constant init. */
9392
9393 /* If the type has (or might have) a mutable component, that component
9394 might be modified. */
9395 if (TYPE_HAS_MUTABLE_P (type) || !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
9396 type_quals &= ~TYPE_QUAL_CONST;
9397
9398 c_apply_type_quals_to_decl (type_quals, decl);
9399}
9400
9401/* Subroutine of casts_away_constness. Make T1 and T2 point at
9402 exemplar types such that casting T1 to T2 is casting away constness
9403 if and only if there is no implicit conversion from T1 to T2. */
9404
9405static void
9406casts_away_constness_r (tree *t1, tree *t2, tsubst_flags_t complain)
9407{
9408 int quals1;
9409 int quals2;
9410
9411 /* [expr.const.cast]
9412
9413 For multi-level pointer to members and multi-level mixed pointers
9414 and pointers to members (conv.qual), the "member" aspect of a
9415 pointer to member level is ignored when determining if a const
9416 cv-qualifier has been cast away. */
9417 /* [expr.const.cast]
9418
9419 For two pointer types:
9420
9421 X1 is T1cv1,1 * ... cv1,N * where T1 is not a pointer type
9422 X2 is T2cv2,1 * ... cv2,M * where T2 is not a pointer type
9423 K is min(N,M)
9424
9425 casting from X1 to X2 casts away constness if, for a non-pointer
9426 type T there does not exist an implicit conversion (clause
9427 _conv_) from:
9428
9429 Tcv1,(N-K+1) * cv1,(N-K+2) * ... cv1,N *
9430
9431 to
9432
9433 Tcv2,(M-K+1) * cv2,(M-K+2) * ... cv2,M *. */
9434 if ((!TYPE_PTR_P (*t1) && !TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (*t1))
9435 || (!TYPE_PTR_P (*t2) && !TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (*t2)))
9436 {
9437 *t1 = cp_build_qualified_type (void_type_node,
9438 cp_type_quals (*t1));
9439 *t2 = cp_build_qualified_type (void_type_node,
9440 cp_type_quals (*t2));
9441 return;
9442 }
9443
9444 quals1 = cp_type_quals (*t1);
9445 quals2 = cp_type_quals (*t2);
9446
9447 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (*t1))
9448 *t1 = TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (*t1);
9449 else
9450 *t1 = TREE_TYPE (*t1);
9451 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (*t2))
9452 *t2 = TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (*t2);
9453 else
9454 *t2 = TREE_TYPE (*t2);
9455
9456 casts_away_constness_r (t1, t2, complain);
9457 *t1 = build_pointer_type (*t1);
9458 *t2 = build_pointer_type (*t2);
9459 *t1 = cp_build_qualified_type (*t1, quals1);
9460 *t2 = cp_build_qualified_type (*t2, quals2);
9461}
9462
9463/* Returns nonzero if casting from TYPE1 to TYPE2 casts away
9464 constness.
9465
9466 ??? This function returns non-zero if casting away qualifiers not
9467 just const. We would like to return to the caller exactly which
9468 qualifiers are casted away to give more accurate diagnostics.
9469*/
9470
9471static bool
9472casts_away_constness (tree t1, tree t2, tsubst_flags_t complain)
9473{
9474 if (TREE_CODE (t2) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
9475 {
9476 /* [expr.const.cast]
9477
9478 Casting from an lvalue of type T1 to an lvalue of type T2
9479 using a reference cast casts away constness if a cast from an
9480 rvalue of type "pointer to T1" to the type "pointer to T2"
9481 casts away constness. */
9482 t1 = (TREE_CODE (t1) == REFERENCE_TYPE ? TREE_TYPE (t1) : t1);
9483 return casts_away_constness (build_pointer_type (t1),
9484 build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (t2)),
9485 complain);
9486 }
9487
9488 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (t1) && TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (t2))
9489 /* [expr.const.cast]
9490
9491 Casting from an rvalue of type "pointer to data member of X
9492 of type T1" to the type "pointer to data member of Y of type
9493 T2" casts away constness if a cast from an rvalue of type
9494 "pointer to T1" to the type "pointer to T2" casts away
9495 constness. */
9496 return casts_away_constness
9497 (build_pointer_type (TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (t1)),
9498 build_pointer_type (TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (t2)),
9499 complain);
9500
9501 /* Casting away constness is only something that makes sense for
9502 pointer or reference types. */
9503 if (!TYPE_PTR_P (t1) || !TYPE_PTR_P (t2))
9504 return false;
9505
9506 /* Top-level qualifiers don't matter. */
9507 t1 = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t1);
9508 t2 = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t2);
9509 casts_away_constness_r (&t1, &t2, complain);
9510 if (!can_convert (t2, t1, complain))
9511 return true;
9512
9513 return false;
9514}
9515
9516/* If T is a REFERENCE_TYPE return the type to which T refers.
9517 Otherwise, return T itself. */
9518
9519tree
9520non_reference (tree t)
9521{
9522 if (t && TREE_CODE (t) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
9523 t = TREE_TYPE (t);
9524 return t;
9525}
9526
9527
9528/* Return nonzero if REF is an lvalue valid for this language;
9529 otherwise, print an error message and return zero. USE says
9530 how the lvalue is being used and so selects the error message. */
9531
9532int
9533lvalue_or_else (tree ref, enum lvalue_use use, tsubst_flags_t complain)
9534{
9535 cp_lvalue_kind kind = lvalue_kind (ref);
9536
9537 if (kind == clk_none)
9538 {
9539 if (complain & tf_error)
9540 lvalue_error (input_location, use);
9541 return 0;
9542 }
9543 else if (kind & (clk_rvalueref|clk_class))
9544 {
9545 if (!(complain & tf_error))
9546 return 0;
9547 if (kind & clk_class)
9548 /* Make this a permerror because we used to accept it. */
9549 permerror (input_location, "using temporary as lvalue");
9550 else
9551 error ("using xvalue (rvalue reference) as lvalue");
9552 }
9553 return 1;
9554}
9555
9556/* Return true if a user-defined literal operator is a raw operator. */
9557
9558bool
9559check_raw_literal_operator (const_tree decl)
9560{
9561 tree argtypes = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (decl));
9562 tree argtype;
9563 int arity;
9564 bool maybe_raw_p = false;
9565
9566 /* Count the number and type of arguments and check for ellipsis. */
9567 for (argtype = argtypes, arity = 0;
9568 argtype && argtype != void_list_node;
9569 ++arity, argtype = TREE_CHAIN (argtype))
9570 {
9571 tree t = TREE_VALUE (argtype);
9572
9573 if (same_type_p (t, const_string_type_node))
9574 maybe_raw_p = true;
9575 }
9576 if (!argtype)
9577 return false; /* Found ellipsis. */
9578
9579 if (!maybe_raw_p || arity != 1)
9580 return false;
9581
9582 return true;
9583}
9584
9585
9586/* Return true if a user-defined literal operator has one of the allowed
9587 argument types. */
9588
9589bool
9590check_literal_operator_args (const_tree decl,
9591 bool *long_long_unsigned_p, bool *long_double_p)
9592{
9593 tree argtypes = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (decl));
9594
9595 *long_long_unsigned_p = false;
9596 *long_double_p = false;
9597 if (processing_template_decl || processing_specialization)
9598 return argtypes == void_list_node;
9599 else
9600 {
9601 tree argtype;
9602 int arity;
9603 int max_arity = 2;
9604
9605 /* Count the number and type of arguments and check for ellipsis. */
9606 for (argtype = argtypes, arity = 0;
9607 argtype && argtype != void_list_node;
9608 argtype = TREE_CHAIN (argtype))
9609 {
9610 tree t = TREE_VALUE (argtype);
9611 ++arity;
9612
9613 if (TYPE_PTR_P (t))
9614 {
9615 bool maybe_raw_p = false;
9616 t = TREE_TYPE (t);
9617 if (cp_type_quals (t) != TYPE_QUAL_CONST)
9618 return false;
9619 t = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t);
9620 if ((maybe_raw_p = same_type_p (t, char_type_node))
9621 || same_type_p (t, wchar_type_node)
9622 || same_type_p (t, char16_type_node)
9623 || same_type_p (t, char32_type_node))
9624 {
9625 argtype = TREE_CHAIN (argtype);
9626 if (!argtype)
9627 return false;
9628 t = TREE_VALUE (argtype);
9629 if (maybe_raw_p && argtype == void_list_node)
9630 return true;
9631 else if (same_type_p (t, size_type_node))
9632 {
9633 ++arity;
9634 continue;
9635 }
9636 else
9637 return false;
9638 }
9639 }
9640 else if (same_type_p (t, long_long_unsigned_type_node))
9641 {
9642 max_arity = 1;
9643 *long_long_unsigned_p = true;
9644 }
9645 else if (same_type_p (t, long_double_type_node))
9646 {
9647 max_arity = 1;
9648 *long_double_p = true;
9649 }
9650 else if (same_type_p (t, char_type_node))
9651 max_arity = 1;
9652 else if (same_type_p (t, wchar_type_node))
9653 max_arity = 1;
9654 else if (same_type_p (t, char16_type_node))
9655 max_arity = 1;
9656 else if (same_type_p (t, char32_type_node))
9657 max_arity = 1;
9658 else
9659 return false;
9660 }
9661 if (!argtype)
9662 return false; /* Found ellipsis. */
9663
9664 if (arity != max_arity)
9665 return false;
9666
9667 return true;
9668 }
9669}
9670
9671/* Always returns false since unlike C90, C++ has no concept of implicit
9672 function declarations. */
9673
9674bool
9675c_decl_implicit (const_tree)
9676{
9677 return false;
9678}
